t\n   187→bun run lint:strict  # Zero warnings tolerance\n   188→\n   189→# Formatting\n   190→bun run format       # Format with Prettier\n   191→bun run format:check # Check formatting\n   192→\n   193→# Git hooks\n   194→bun run prepare      # Install Husky hooks\n   195→```\n   196→\n   197→---\n   198→\n   199→## Environment Configuration\n   200→\n   201→Copy `env.example.txt` to `.env.local` and configure:\n   202→\n   203→### Required for Authentication (Clerk)\n   204→\n   205→```env\n   206→NEXT_PUBLIC_CLERK_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=pk_...\n   207→CLERK_SECRET_KEY=sk_...\n   208→\n   209→# Redirect URLs\n   210→NEXT_PUBLIC_CLERK_SIGN_IN_URL=\"/auth/sign-in\"\n   211→NEXT_PUBLIC_CLERK_SIGN_UP_URL=\"/auth/sign-up\"\n   212→NEXT_PUBLIC_CLERK_AFTER_SIGN_IN_URL=\"/dashboard/overview\"\n   213→NEXT_PUBLIC_CLERK_AFTER_SIGN_UP_URL=\"/dashboard/overview\"\n   214→```\n   215→\n   216→### Optional for Error Tracking (Sentry)\n   217→\n   218→```env\n   219→NEXT_PUBLIC_SENTRY_DSN=https://...@....ingest.sentry.io/...\n   220→NEXT_PUBLIC_SENTRY_ORG=your-org\n   221→NEXT_PUBLIC_SENTRY_PROJECT=your-project\n   222→SENTRY_AUTH_TOKEN=sntrys_...\n   223→NEXT_PUBLIC_SENTRY_DISABLED=\"false\"  # Set to \"true\" to disable in dev\n   224→```\n   225→\n   226→**Note**: Clerk supports \"keyless mode\" - the app works without API keys for initial development.\n   227→\n   228→---\n   229→\n   230→## Code Style Guidelines\n   231→\n   232→### TypeScript\n   233→\n   234→- Strict mode enabled\n   235→- Use explicit return types for public functions\n   236→- Prefer interface over type for object definitions\n   237→- Use `@/*` alias for imports from src\n   238→\n   239→### Formatting (Prettier)\n   240→\n   241→```json\n   242→{\n   243→  \"singleQuote\": true,\n   244→  \"jsxSingleQuote\": true,\n   245→  \"semi\": true,\n   246→  \"trailingComma\": \"none\",\n   247→  \"tabWidth\": 2,\n   248→  \"arrowParens\": \"always\"\n   249→}\n   250→```\n   251→\n   252→### ESLint Rules\n   253→\n   254→- `@typescript-eslint/no-unused-vars`: warn\n   255→- `no-console`: warn\n   256→- `react-hooks/exhaustive-deps`: warn\n   257→- `import/no-unresolved`: off (handled by TypeScript)\n   258→\n   259→### Component Conventions\n   260→\n   261→- Use function declarations for components: `function ComponentName() {}`\n   262→- Props interface named `{ComponentName}Props`\n   263→- shadcn/ui components use `cn()` utility for class merging\n   264→- Server components by default, `'use client'` only when needed\n   265→\n   266→---\n   267→\n   268→## Theming System\n   269→\n   270→The project uses a sophisticated multi-theme system with 10 built-in themes:\n   271→\n   272→- `vercel` (default)\n   273→- `claude`\n   274→- `neobrutualism`\n   275→- `supabase`\n   276→- `mono`\n   277→- `notebook`\n   278→- `light-green`\n   279→- `zen`\n   280→- `astro-vista`\n   281→- `whatsapp`\n   282→\n   283→### Theme Files\n   284→\n   285→- CSS files: `src/styles/themes/{theme-name}.css`\n   286→- Theme registry: `src/components/themes/theme.config.ts`\n   287→- Font config: `src/components/themes/font.config.ts`\n   288→- Active theme provider: `src/components/themes/active-theme.tsx`\n   289→\n   290→### Adding a New Theme\n   291→\n   292→1. Create `src/styles/themes/your-theme.css` with `[data-theme='your-theme']` selector\n   293→2. Import in `src/styles/theme.css`\n   294→3. Add to `THEMES` array in `src/components/themes/theme.config.ts`\n   295→4. (Optional) Add fonts in `font.config.ts`\n   296→5. (Optional) Set as default in `theme.config.ts`\n   297→\n   298→See `docs/themes.md` for detailed theming guide.\n   299→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_0133G6eTKKyED961Dh5CjooQ","session_id":"b1ad336c-66a2-4f3f-98dd-2e5d8c4f5736","uuid":"1e624a8c-50a3-4f98-8e5b-91b751ff07f2"}
