{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_0133G6eTKKyED961Dh5CjooQ","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information needed. Let me provide you with a comprehensive exploration report.\n\n---\n\n## Project Structure Exploration - Complete Report\n\nI've conducted a thorough exploration of your Next.js 16 + shadcn/ui dashboard starter. Here's what I found:\n\n### 1. Overall Directory Layout\n\n**Root level structure:**\n```\n/src\n├── app/              # Next.js App Router (pages, layouts, API routes)\n├── components/       # Reusable UI components (layout, forms, themes, icons)\n├── features/         # Feature-based modules (auth, products, users, chat, kanban, profile)\n├── config/           # Configuration files (nav-config.ts, infoconfig.ts, data-table.ts)\n├── constants/        # Constants and mock data\n├── hooks/            # Custom React hooks (use-data-table, use-nav, use-breadcrumbs, etc.)\n├── lib/              # Utility functions and query client setup\n├── styles/           # Global CSS and theme files (10 built-in themes)\n├── types/            # TypeScript type definitions\n├── instrumentation.ts   # Server instrumentation\n├── instrumentation-client.ts # Client instrumentation\n└── proxy.ts          # Clerk middleware configuration\n```\n\n### 2. Clerk Authentication Setup - Complete Overview\n\n**Clerk is fully integrated with the following imports found across the codebase:**\n\n**Key Clerk files and their locations:**\n\n| File Path | Purpose |\n|-----------|---------|\n| `/src/proxy.ts` | Middleware setup with `clerkMiddleware` and protected route matcher |\n| `/src/components/layout/providers.tsx` | Root `<ClerkProvider>` wrapper with theme integration |\n| `/src/app/auth/` | Auth routes (sign-in, sign-up with catch-all routing) |\n| `/src/features/auth/components/` | Auth components (sign-in-view, sign-up-view) |\n| `/src/config/nav-config.ts` | Navigation RBAC configuration |\n| `/src/hooks/use-nav.ts` | Hook for navigation filtering with Clerk RBAC |\n\n**Clerk integration points:**\n\n- **Client components using Clerk hooks:** `useUser()`, `useAuth()`, `useOrganization()`, `useOrganizationList()`\n- **Server-side auth:** `auth()` from `@clerk/nextjs/server` (in root layout, dashboard page)\n- **Auth components:** `SignIn`, `SignUp`, `UserProfile`, `OrganizationProfile`, `OrganizationList`, `PricingTable`\n- **Protected routes:** `<Protect>` component for feature/plan-based access control\n- **Sign out:** `<SignOutButton>` component\n- **Theme integration:** Dark theme from `@clerk/themes` applied in providers.tsx\n\n**Clerk-specific configurations in providers.tsx:**\n\n```typescript\n<ClerkProvider\n  appearance={{\n    baseTheme: resolvedTheme === 'dark' ? dark : undefined,\n    variables: {\n      colorPrimary, colorDanger, colorBackground, \n      colorForeground, colorMuted, colorInput, \n      colorBorder, colorRing, fontFamily\n      // All using CSS custom properties\n    }\n  }}\n>\n```\n\n### 3. Providers.tsx File Details\n\n**Location:** `/src/components/layout/providers.tsx`\n\n**Structure:**\n- Client component (`'use client'`)\n- Wraps: `ActiveThemeProvider` → `ClerkProvider` → `QueryProvider` → children\n- Receives `activeThemeValue` prop from root layout\n- Integrates theme with Clerk appearance settings\n- Uses `next-themes` for theme resolution\n\n**Dependency chain:** ClerkProvider wraps QueryProvider which wraps the actual page content\n\n### 4. Package.json Dependencies\n\n**Key versions:**\n- Next.js: `16.2.1`\n- React: `19.2.4`\n- TypeScript: `5.7.2`\n- Tailwind CSS: `^4.2.2`\n- Clerk: `@clerk/nextjs: ^6.39.1`\n- Clerk themes: `@clerk/themes: ^2.4.57`\n- React Query: `@tanstack/react-query: ^5.95.2`\n- React Form: `@tanstack/react-form: ^1.28.5`\n- React Table: `@tanstack/react-table: ^8.21.3`\n- Zod: `^4.3.6`\n- Zustand: `^5.0.12`\n- nuqs: `^2.8.9` (URL search params)\n- Sentry: `@sentry/nextjs: ^10.45.0`\n- Recharts: `^2.15.4` (charts)\n- next-themes: `^0.4.6`\n- dnd-kit: `^6.3.1`, `^9.0.0`, `^10.0.0` (drag-and-drop)\n\n**Dev dependencies:** oxlint, oxfmt (for linting/formatting), husky, lint-staged, faker\n\n### 5. Database Configuration\n\n**Current setup:** NO persistent database configured\n- Using **mock data** at `/src/constants/mock-api-users.ts` and similar\n- API routes at `/src/app/api/` demonstrate patterns for:\n  - Route Handlers + ORM (fullstack pattern)\n  - BFF/proxy pattern (backend-for-frontend)\n  - Mock data (current demo)\n\n**Example from `/src/app/api/users/route.ts`:**\n```typescript\n// Comments indicate where to swap:\n// Replace fakeUsers with db.query.users (ORM)\n// Or fetch from external backend\n// Currently using in-memory fake data\n```\n\n**No Prisma schema or .env configuration files present** - ready for you to add your database\n\n### 6. TypeScript and Next.js Configuration\n\n**tsconfig.json:**\n- Strict mode: `true`\n- Target: `ES2017`\n- Module: `esnext`\n- Path alias: `@/*` → `./src/*`\n- JSX: `react-jsx`\n- Plugin: Next.js plugin\n\n**next.config.ts:**\n- Sentry integration (conditional, can be disabled)\n- Image remotePatterns for: `api.slingacademy.com`, `img.clerk.com`, `clerk.com`\n- Standalone output (optional via `BUILD_STANDALONE` env var)\n- Console removal in production\n- geist package transpilation\n\n### 7. Global CSS File Location\n\n**Location:** `/src/styles/globals.css`\n\n**Contents:**\n- Tailwind imports (`@import 'tailwindcss'`)\n- Tailwind animate CSS\n- Custom scrollbar styling\n- View transition animation (reveal effect)\n- Base layer CSS custom properties\n\n**Theme system:**\n- Theme imports in: `/src/styles/theme.css`\n- Individual themes in: `/src/styles/themes/{theme-name}.css` (10 themes available)\n- Font configuration: `/src/components/themes/font.config.ts`\n- Theme registry: `/src/components/themes/theme.config.ts`\n- Default theme: `vercel`, applied via `data-theme` attribute on `<html>`\n\n### Key Authentication Flow\n\n1. **User visits app** → Root layout reads cookie `active_theme`\n2. **Providers.tsx wraps content** → ClerkProvider with theme customization\n3. **proxy.ts middleware** → Checks if route is protected (`/dashboard(.*)`)\n4. **Protected routes** → Call `auth.protect()` to ensure user is logged in\n5. **Navigation RBAC** → `useNav` hook filters nav items based on Clerk org/role/permissions\n\n### API Structure Pattern\n\nFound in `/src/features/products/api/` and `/src/features/users/api/`:\n```\napi/\n├── types.ts      # Type contracts (response shapes, filters)\n├── service.ts    # Data access layer (swap for your backend)\n├── queries.ts    # React Query options + key factories\n└── mutations.ts  # Mutation options (if applicable)\n```\n\n### Important Notes\n\n- **No middleware.ts** - Clerk uses `proxy.ts` instead (via `clerkMiddleware`)\n- **No Prisma** - Project is template-ready, designed to work with any backend\n- **Environment variables** - Expected keys in AGENTS.md: `NEXT_PUBLIC_CLERK_PUBLISHABLE_KEY`, `CLERK_SECRET_KEY`, optional Sentry variables\n- **Theme cookie** - Stored as `active_theme` in cookies, persisted across sessions\n- **No database schema** - This is intentional - the template is backend-agnostic\n\n---\n\n## File Paths Summary (Absolute Paths)\n\n- **Providers:** `/src/components/layout/providers.tsx`\n- **Global CSS:** `/src/styles/globals.css`\n- **Config files:** `/src/config/nav-config.ts`, `/src/config/infoconfig.ts`\n- **Clerk middleware:** `/src/proxy.ts`\n- **Root layout:** `/src/app/layout.tsx`\n- **Auth routes:** `/src/app/auth/`\n- **Auth components:** `/src/features/auth/components/`\n- **Theme system:** `/src/components/themes/`, `/src/styles/themes/`\n- **TypeScript config:** `/tsconfig.json`\n- **Next.js config:** `/next.config.ts`\n- **Package config:** `/package.json`\n- **Documentation:** `/docs/clerk_setup.md`, `/AGENTS.md`"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a3ee67406c9fbc79d (for resuming 