{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_019RDPBUa17D2eivSNWxMGRt","type":"tool_result","content":"# Drizzle ORM Adapter Setup for Better Auth\n\n## 1. Required Packages\n\nInstall the Drizzle adapter package:\n\n```bash\nnpm install @better-auth/drizzle-adapter\n```\n\nYou'll also need Drizzle ORM itself. Refer to the [Drizzle Documentation](https://orm.drizzle.team/docs/overview/) for complete setup instructions.\n\n## 2. Configuration in auth.ts\n\nBasic adapter setup with provider selection:\n\n```typescript\nimport { betterAuth } from \"better-auth\";\nimport { drizzleAdapter } from \"better-auth/adapters/drizzle\";\nimport { db } from \"./database.ts\";\n\nexport const auth = betterAuth({\n  database: drizzleAdapter(db, { \n    provider: \"sqlite\", // or \"pg\" or \"mysql\"\n  }), \n  // ... rest of configuration\n});\n```\n\n## 3. Schema Generation\n\nGenerate the required database schema automatically:\n\n```bash\nnpx auth@latest generate\n```\n\nThis command creates the necessary tables based on your Better Auth configuration.\n\n## 4. Database Table Structure\n\nThe adapter automatically manages core tables including:\n- **user** - stores user information\n- **session** - manages user sessions\n- **account** - handles OAuth/social account linking\n- **verification** - manages email and other verification tokens\n\n## 5. SQLite-Specific Configuration\n\nFor SQLite implementations, specify the provider in the adapter options. The adapter handles provider-specific syntax automatically based on your selection (\"sqlite\", \"pg\", or \"mysql\").\n\n**Optional: Plural Table Names**\n\nIf your schema uses plural naming conventions:\n\n```typescript\ndatabase: drizzleAdapter(db, {\n  provider: \"sqlite\",\n  usePlural: true,\n})\n```"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b1ad336c-66a2-4f3f-98dd-2e5d8c4f5736","uuid":"e0947cb5-6c9f-4ef8-84c2-f1d2884433ce","tool_use_result":{"bytes":305797,"code":200,"codeText":"OK","result":"# Drizzle ORM Adapter Setup for Better Auth\n\n## 1. Required Packages\n\nInstall the Drizzle adapter package:\n\n```bash\nnpm install @better-auth/drizzle-adapter\n```\n\nYou'll also need Drizzle ORM itself. Refer to the [Drizzle Documentation](https://orm.drizzle.team/docs/overview/) for complete setup instructions.\n\n## 2. Configuration in auth.ts\n\nBasic adapter setup with provider selection:\n\n```typescript\nimport { betterAuth } from \"better-auth\";\nimport { drizzleAdapter } from \"better-auth/adapters/drizzle\";\nimport { db } from \"./database.ts\";\n\nexport const auth = betterAuth({\n  database: drizzleAdapter(db, { \n    provider: \"sqlite\", // or \"pg\" or \"mysql\"\n  }), \n  // ... rest of configuration\n});\n```\n\n## 3. Schema Generation\n\nGenerate the required database schema automatically:\n\n```bash\nnpx auth@latest generate\n```\n\nThis command creates the necessary tables based on your Better Auth configuration.\n\n## 4. Database Table Structure\n\nThe adapter automatically manages core tables including:\n- **user** - stores user information\n- **session** - manages user sessions\n- **account** - handles OAuth/social account linking\n- **verification** - manages email and other verification tokens\n\n## 5. SQLite-Specific Configuration\n\nFor SQLite implementations, specify the provider in the adapter options. The adapter handles provider-specific syntax automatically based on your selection (\"sqlite\", \"pg\", or \"mysql\").\n\n**Optional: Plural Table Names**\n\nIf your schema uses plural naming conventions:\n\n```typescript\ndatabase: drizzleAdapter(db, {\n  provider: \"sqlite\",\n  usePlural: true,\n})\n```","durationMs":5528,"url":"https://www.better-auth.com/docs/adapters/drizzle"}}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Y1M2WuXPqt5QUDWt57ZpLe","type":"tool_result","content":"# Better Auth Installation & Setup Guide for Next.js\n\n## 1. Package Installation\n\nInstall Better Auth in your project:\n```bash\nnpm install better-auth\n```\n\nFor a separate client-server setup, install in both parts of your project.\n\n## 2. Environment Variables\n\nCreate a `.env` file in your project root with:\n\n```env\nBETTER_AUTH_SECRET=your-generated-secret-key\nBETTER_AUTH_URL=http://localhost:3000\n```\n\nGenerate a secret using: `openssl rand -base64 32`\n\n## 3. Server Configuration (auth.ts)\n\nCreate `lib/auth.ts` (or `utils/auth.ts`):\n\n```typescript\nimport { betterAuth } from \"better-auth\";\nimport Database from \"better-sqlite3\";\n\nexport const auth = betterAuth({\n  database: new Database(\"./sqlite.db\"),\n  emailAndPassword: { \n    enabled: true, \n  }, \n});\n```\n\nAlternative with Drizzle ORM:\n```typescript\nimport { drizzleAdapter } from \"better-auth/adapters/drizzle\";\nimport { db } from \"@/db\";\n\nexport const auth = betterAuth({\n  database: drizzleAdapter(db, { provider: \"sqlite\" }),\n});\n```\n\n## 4. API Route Setup (Next.js App Router)\n\nCreate `/app/api/auth/[...all]/route.ts`:\n\n```typescript\nimport { auth } from \"@/lib/auth\";\nimport { toNextJsHandler } from \"better-auth/next-js\";\n\nexport const { POST, GET } = toNextJsHandler(auth);\n```\n\nThis handles all authentication requests at `/api/auth/*`.\n\n## 5. Database Setup\n\nRun CLI commands to create tables:\n\n```bash\nnpx auth@latest generate\nnpx auth@latest migrate\n```\n\nThe system supports SQLite, PostgreSQL, MySQL, MongoDB, and popular ORMs like Prisma and Drizzle.\n\n## 6. Client Configuration (auth-client.ts)\n\nCreate `lib/auth-client.ts`:\n\n```typescript\nimport { createAuthClient } from \"better-auth/react\";\n\nexport const authClient = createAuthClient({\n  baseURL: \"http://localhost:3000\"\n});\n```\n\nExport specific methods if preferred:\n```typescript\nexport const { signIn, signUp, useSession } = createAuthClient();\n```\n\n## 7. Implementation Complete\n\nAfter configuration, you're ready to use authentication methods like sign-in, sign-up, and session management throughout your Next.js application. Continue with the basic usage documentation for practical examples."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b1ad336c-66a2-4f3f-98dd-2e5d8c4f5736","uuid":"e015ed9a-24cd-4135-bbd3-b97cd33c11ef","tool_use_result":{"bytes":618532,"code":200,"codeText":"OK","result":"# Better Auth Installation & Setup Guide for Next.js\n\n## 1. Package Installation\n\nInstall Better Auth in your project:\n```bash\nnpm install better-auth\n```\n\nFor a separate client-server setup, install in both parts of your project.\n\n## 2. Environment Variables\n\nCreate a `.env` file in your project root with:\n\n```env\nBETTER_AUTH_SECRET=your-generated-secret-key\nBETTER_AUTH_URL=http://localhost:3000\n```\n\nGenerate a secret using: `openssl rand -base64 32`\n\n## 3. Server Configuration (auth.ts)\n\nCreate `lib/auth.ts` (or `utils/auth.ts`):\n\n```typescript\nimport { betterAuth } from \"better-auth\";\nimport Database from \"better-sqlite3\";\n\nexport const auth = betterAuth({\n  database: new Database(\"./sqlite.db\"),\n  emailAndPassword: { \n    enabled: true, \n  }, \n});\n```\n\nAlternative with Drizzle ORM:\n```typescript\nimport { drizzleAdapter } from \"better-auth/adapters/drizzle\";\nimport { db } from \"@/db\";\n\nexport const auth = betterAuth({\n  database: drizzleAdapter(db, { provider: \"sqlite\" }),\n});\n```\n\n## 4. API Route Setup (Next.js App Router)\n\nCreate `/app/api/auth/[...all]/route.ts`:\n\n```typescript\nimport { auth } from \"@/lib/auth\";\nimport { toNextJsHandler } from \"better-auth/next-js\";\n\nexport const { POST, GET } = toNextJsHandler(auth);\n```\n\nThis handles all authentication requests at `/api/auth/*`.\n\n## 5. Database Setup\n\nRun CLI commands to create tables:\n\n```bash\nnpx auth@latest generate\nnpx auth@latest migrate\n```\n\nThe system supports SQLite, PostgreSQL, MySQL, MongoDB, and popular ORMs like Prisma and Drizzle.\n\n## 6. Client Configuration (auth-client.ts)\n\nCreate `lib/auth-client.ts`:\n\n```typescript\nimport { createAuthClient } from \"better-auth/react\";\n\nexport const authClient = createAuthClient({\n  baseURL: \"http://localhost:3000\"\n});\n```\n\nExport specific methods if preferred:\n```typescript\nexport const { signIn, signUp, useSession } = createAuthClient();\n```\n\n## 7. Implementation Complete\n\nAfter configuration, you're ready to use authentication methods like sign-in, sign-up, and session management throughout your Next.js application. Continue with the basic usage documentation for practical examples.","durationMs":7084,"url":"https://www.better-auth.com/docs/installation"}}
