{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01H5WebFQx4wS56jQUhR3G2c","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→{\n     2→  \"project\": \"Replace Clerk with Better-Auth\",\n     3→  \"description\": \"Fully replace Clerk (third-party auth service) with better-auth (self-hosted, TypeScript-first auth library) across the entire Next.js dashboard. This migrates authentication, organizations, RBAC, and billing from a SaaS dependency to an in-house solution using SQLite, better-auth plugins, and better-auth-ui components. The result is zero vendor lock-in, no per-user pricing, and full control over auth data.\",\n     4→  \"userStories\": [\n     5→    {\n     6→      \"id\": \"US-001\",\n     7→      \"title\": \"Set up better-auth server config and database\",\n     8→      \"description\": \"As a developer, I need the better-auth server configuration with SQLite so that auth data is stored locally and all plugins are initialized.\",\n     9→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n    10→        \"lib/auth.ts created with betterAuth() config: SQLite via Drizzle adapter, emailAndPassword: { enabled: true }, nextCookies() plugin\",\n    11→        \"Drizzle ORM configured with better-sqlite3 driver and @libsql/client\",\n    12→        \"Database schema generated via npx auth@latest generate and migrations applied via drizzle-kit\",\n    13→        \"Core tables exist: user, session, account, verification\",\n    14→        \"lib/auth-client.ts created with createAuthClient() for client-side usage\",\n    15→        \"API catch-all route at app/api/auth/[...all]/route.ts using toNextJsHandler(auth)\",\n    16→        \"Environment variables documented in env.example.txt (database path, auth secret)\",\n    17→        \"Typecheck passes\"\n    18→      ],\n    19→      \"priority\": 1,\n    20→      \"passes\": false,\n    21→      \"inProgress\": true\n    22→    },\n    23→    {\n    24→      \"id\": \"US-002\",\n    25→      \"title\": \"Set up better-auth-ui provider\",\n    26→      \"description\": \"As a developer, I need the AuthUIProvider wired into the app so that better-auth-ui components work throughout the dashboard.\",\n    27→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n    28→        \"@daveyplate/better-auth-ui installed\",\n    29→        \"@import \\\"@daveyplate/better-auth-ui/css\\\" added to global CSS (if TailwindCSS v4)\",\n    30→        \"\\u003cAuthUIProvider\\u003e wraps the app in providers.tsx, replacing \\u003cClerkProvider\\u003e\",\n    31→        \"Provider configured with authClient, navigate, replace, onSessionChange, and Link\",\n    32→        \"\\u003cClerkProvider\\u003e and all @clerk/themes imports removed from providers.tsx\",\n    33→        \"Typecheck passes\"\n    34→      ],\n    35→      \"priority\": 2,\n    36→      \"passes\": false\n    37→    },\n    38→    {\n    39→      \"id\": \"US-003\",\n    40→      \"title\": \"Replace sign-in and sign-up pages\",\n    41→      \"description\": \"As a user, I want to sign in and sign up with email/password so that I can access the dashboard.\",\n    42→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n    43→        \"Auth routes restructured: app/auth/[path]/page.tsx renders \\u003cAuthView /\\u003e from better-auth-ui\",\n    44→        \"Sign-in page works at /auth/sign-in\",\n    45→        \"Sign-up page works at /auth/sign-up\",\n    46→        \"Forgot password flow works at /auth/forgot-password\",\n    47→        \"Successful sign-in redirects to /dashboard/overview\",\n    48→        \"Clerk \\u003cSignIn\\u003e and \\u003cSignUp\\u003e components removed from src/features/auth/components/\",\n    49→        \"Old Clerk catch-all routes ([[...sign-in]], [[...sign-up]]) removed\",\n    50→        \"Typecheck passes\"\n    51→      ],\n    52→      \"priority\": 3,\n    53→      \"passes\": false\n    54→    },\n    55→    {\n    56→      \"id\": \"US-004\",\n    57→      \"title\": \"Replace server-side auth checks\",\n    58→      \"description\": \"As a developer, I need server-side session validation so that unauthenticated users are redirected to sign-in.\",\n    59→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n    60→        \"app/dashboard/page.tsx uses auth.api.getSession({ headers: await headers() }) instead of Clerk's auth()\",\n    61→        \"app/page.tsx uses the same pattern\",\n    62→        \"Unauthenticated users redirected to /auth/sign-in\",\n    63→        \"Middleware created at middleware.ts using getSessionCookie() for fast cookie-based route protection on /dashboard/*\",\n    64→        \"All imports of @clerk/nextjs server functions removed\",\n    65→        \"Typecheck passes\"\n    66→      ],\n    67→      \"priority\": 4,\n    68→      \"passes\": false\n    69→    },\n    70→    {\n    71→      \"id\": \"US-005\",\n    72→      \"title\": \"Replace user UI components (avatar, nav, sign-out)\",\n    73→      \"description\": \"As a user, I want to see my profile info in the sidebar and header and be able to sign out.\",\n    74→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n    75→        \"app-sidebar.tsx uses better-auth session data (via authClient.useSession()) instead of Clerk's useUser()\",\n    76→        \"user-nav.tsx uses better-auth session data instead of Clerk's useUser()\",\n    77→        \"Sign-out uses authClient.signOut() instead of Clerk's \\u003cSignOutButton\\u003e\",\n    78→        \"\\u003cUserButton /\\u003e from better-auth-ui used where appropriate (or custom implementation using session data)\",\n    79→        \"User name and avatar display correctly\",\n    80→        \"Typecheck passes\"\n    81→      ],\n    82→      \"priority\": 5,\n    83→      \"passes\": false\n    84→    },\n    85→    {\n    86→      \"id\": \"US-006\",\n    87→      \"title\": \"Add organization plugin and replace org features\",\n    88→      \"description\": \"As a user, I want to create and switch between organizations so that I can manage team workspaces.\",\n    89→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n    90→        \"Organization plugin added to lib/auth.ts with roles: owner, admin, member\",\n    91→        \"organizationClient() plugin added to lib/auth-client.ts\",\n    92→        \"Organization tables generated and migrated (organization, member, invitation)\",\n    93→        \"\\u003cOrganizationSwitcher /\\u003e from better-auth-ui replaces custom org-switcher.tsx (or rebuilt with better-auth data)\",\n    94→        \"/dashboard/workspaces page uses better-auth-ui org components instead of Clerk's \\u003cOrganizationList\\u003e\",\n    95→        \"/dashboard/workspaces/team page uses better-auth-ui \\u003cOrganizationSettingsCards\\u003e + \\u003cOrganizationMembersCard\\u003e instead of Clerk's \\u003cOrganizationProfile\\u003e\",\n    96→        \"Users can create, switch, and manage organizations\",\n    97→        \"Typecheck passes\"\n    98→      ],\n    99→      \"priority\": 6,\n   100→      \"passes\": false\n   101→    },\n   102→    {\n   103→      \"id\": \"US-007\",\n   104→      \"title\": \"Replace RBAC and nav filtering\",\n   105→      \"description\": \"As a developer, I need role-based access control so that navigation items and pages are restricted by role, permission, and plan.\",\n   106→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n   107→        \"createAccessControl() configured with statements matching current permissions (e.g., org:teams:manage)\",\n   108→        \"Roles defined: owner, admin, member (matching current Clerk roles)\",\n   109→        \"use-nav.ts hook updated: replace useOrganization() and useUser() from Clerk with better-auth equivalents (authClient.useActiveOrganization(), authClient.useSession())\",\n   110→        \"requireOrg check uses better-auth active organization state\",\n   111→        \"permission check uses authClient.organization.hasPermission()\",\n   112→        \"role check uses active member role from better-auth\",\n   113→        \"plan check uses subscription data from better-auth stripe plugin\",\n   114→        \"/dashboard/exclusive page uses better-auth permission check instead of Clerk's \\u003cProtect\\u003e\",\n   115→        \"Nav items still filter correctly based on org, role, and plan\",\n   116→        \"Typecheck passes\"\n   117→      ],\n   118→      \"priority\": 7,\n   119→      \"passes\": false\n   120→    },\n   121→    {\n   122→      \"id\": \"US-008\",\n   123→      \"title\": \"Add Stripe billing plugin and replace billing page\",\n   124→      \"description\": \"As a user, I want to manage my organization's subscription plan so that I can access premium features.\",\n   125→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n   126→        \"@better-auth/stripe installed and configured in lib/auth.ts with Stripe client and webhook secret\",\n   127→        \"stripeClient() plugin added to lib/auth-client.ts\",\n   128→        \"Subscription plans defined (matching current Pro/Free tiers)\",\n   129→        \"Webhook route configured (auto-handled by better-auth at /api/auth/stripe/webhook)\",\n   130→        \"/dashboard/billing page rebuilt with custom shadcn UI showing plans and subscription status (replaces Clerk's \\u003cPricingTable\\u003e)\",\n   131→        \"Users can subscribe, upgrade, cancel via Stripe Checkout\",\n   132→        \"Subscription status accessible for RBAC plan checks\",\n   133→        \"Environment variables added: STRIPE_SECRET_KEY, STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET, plan price IDs\",\n   134→        \"Typecheck passes\"\n   135→      ],\n   136→      \"priority\": 8,\n   137→      \"passes\": false\n   138→    },\n   139→    {\n   140→      \"id\": \"US-009\",\n   141→      \"title\": \"Replace user profile/settings page\",\n   142→      \"description\": \"As a user, I want to manage my account settings (name, email, password) from the dashboard.\",\n   143→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n   144→        \"/dashboard/profile page uses \\u003cAccountSettingsCards /\\u003e and \\u003cSecuritySettingsCards /\\u003e from better-auth-ui instead of Clerk's \\u003cUserProfile\\u003e\",\n   145→        \"User can update name and avatar\",\n   146→        \"User can change password\",\n   147→        \"Typecheck passes\"\n   148→      ],\n   149→      \"priority\": 9,\n   150→      \"passes\": false\n   151→    },\n   152→    {\n   153→      \"id\": \"US-010\",\n   154→      \"title\": \"Remove all Clerk dependencies and clean up\",\n   155→      \"description\": \"As a developer, I want all Clerk code fully removed so there are no dead imports, unused packages, or stale config.\",\n   156→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n   157→        \"@clerk/nextjs and @clerk/themes uninstalled from package.json\",\n   158→        \"Zero imports from @clerk/* anywhere in the codebase (verified via grep)\",\n   159→        \"Clerk environment variables removed from env.example.txt\",\n   160→        \"docs/clerk_setup.md removed or replaced with docs/auth_setup.md for better-auth\",\n   161→        \"docs/nav-rbac.md updated to reference better-auth instead of Clerk\",\n   162→        \"CLAUDE.md and AGENTS.md updated to reference better-auth\",\n   163→        \"PermissionCheck type in src/types/index.ts updated if needed\",\n   164→        \"App builds successfully (next build)\",\n   165→        \"Typecheck passes\",\n   166→        \"No runtime errors on sign-in, sign-up, dashboard, org switching, billing, profile pages\"\n   167→      ],\n   168→      \"priority\": 10,\n   169→      \"passes\": false\n   170→    }\n   171→  ]\n   172→}"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b1ad336c-66a2-4f3f-98dd-2e5d8c4f5736","uuid":"bf3f5956-3189-466e-8917-b22e238a5a12","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/bogdantarasenko/Desktop/hackinterview-tool/next-shadcn-dashboard-starter/.chief/prds/main/prd.json","content":"{\n  \"project\": \"Replace Clerk with Better-Auth\",\n  \"description\": \"Fully replace Clerk (third-party auth service) with better-auth (self-hosted, TypeScript-first auth library) across the entire Next.js dashboard. This migrates authentication, organizations, RBAC, and billing from a SaaS dependency to an in-house solution using SQLite, better-auth plugins, and better-auth-ui components. The result is zero vendor lock-in, no per-user pricing, and full control over auth data.\",\n  \"userStories\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"US-001\",\n      \"title\": \"Set up better-auth server config and database\",\n      \"description\": \"As a developer, I need the better-auth server configuration with SQLite so that auth data is stored locally and all plugins are initialized.\",\n      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n        \"lib/auth.ts created with betterAuth() config: SQLite via Drizzle adapter, emailAndPassword: { enabled: true }, nextCookies() plugin\",\n        \"Drizzle ORM configured with better-sqlite3 driver and @libsql/client\",\n        \"Database schema generated via npx auth@latest generate and migrations applied via drizzle-kit\",\n        \"Core tables exist: user, session, account, verification\",\n        \"lib/auth-client.ts created with createAuthClient() for client-side usage\",\n        \"API catch-all route at app/api/auth/[...all]/route.ts using toNextJsHandler(auth)\",\n        \"Environment variables documented in env.example.txt (database path, auth secret)\",\n        \"Typecheck passes\"\n      ],\n      \"priority\": 1,\n      \"passes\": false,\n      \"inProgress\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"US-002\",\n      \"title\": \"Set up better-auth-ui provider\",\n      \"description\": \"As a developer, I need the AuthUIProvider wired into the app so that better-auth-ui components work throughout the dashboard.\",\n      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n        \"@daveyplate/better-auth-ui installed\",\n        \"@import \\\"@daveyplate/better-auth-ui/css\\\" added to global CSS (if TailwindCSS v4)\",\n        \"\\u003cAuthUIProvider\\u003e wraps the app in providers.tsx, replacing \\u003cClerkProvider\\u003e\",\n        \"Provider configured with authClient, navigate, replace, onSessionChange, and Link\",\n        \"\\u003cClerkProvider\\u003e and all @clerk/themes imports removed from providers.tsx\",\n        \"Typecheck passes\"\n      ],\n      \"priority\": 2,\n      \"passes\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"US-003\",\n      \"title\": \"Replace sign-in and sign-up pages\",\n      \"description\": \"As a user, I want to sign in and sign up with email/password so that I can access the dashboard.\",\n      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n        \"Auth routes restructured: app/auth/[path]/page.tsx renders \\u003cAuthView /\\u003e from better-auth-ui\",\n        \"Sign-in page works at /auth/sign-in\",\n        \"Sign-up page works at /auth/sign-up\",\n        \"Forgot password flow works at /auth/forgot-password\",\n        \"Successful sign-in redirects to /dashboard/overview\",\n        \"Clerk \\u003cSignIn\\u003e and \\u003cSignUp\\u003e components removed from src/features/auth/components/\",\n        \"Old Clerk catch-all routes ([[...sign-in]], [[...sign-up]]) removed\",\n        \"Typecheck passes\"\n      ],\n      \"priority\": 3,\n      \"passes\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"US-004\",\n      \"title\": \"Replace server-side auth checks\",\n      \"description\": \"As a developer, I need server-side session validation so that unauthenticated users are redirected to sign-in.\",\n      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n        \"app/dashboard/page.tsx uses auth.api.getSession({ headers: await headers() }) instead of Clerk's auth()\",\n        \"app/page.tsx uses the same pattern\",\n        \"Unauthenticated users redirected to /auth/sign-in\",\n        \"Middleware created at middleware.ts using getSessionCookie() for fast cookie-based route protection on /dashboard/*\",\n        \"All imports of @clerk/nextjs server functions removed\",\n        \"Typecheck passes\"\n      ],\n      \"priority\": 4,\n      \"passes\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"US-005\",\n      \"title\": \"Replace user UI components (avatar, nav, sign-out)\",\n      \"description\": \"As a user, I want to see my profile info in the sidebar and header and be able to sign out.\",\n      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n        \"app-sidebar.tsx uses better-auth session data (via authClient.useSession()) instead of Clerk's useUser()\",\n        \"user-nav.tsx uses better-auth session data instead of Clerk's useUser()\",\n        \"Sign-out uses authClient.signOut() instead of Clerk's \\u003cSignOutButton\\u003e\",\n        \"\\u003cUserButton /\\u003e from better-auth-ui used where appropriate (or custom implementation using session data)\",\n        \"User name and avatar display correctly\",\n        \"Typecheck passes\"\n      ],\n      \"priority\": 5,\n      \"passes\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"US-006\",\n      \"title\": \"Add organization plugin and replace org features\",\n      \"description\": \"As a user, I want to create and switch between organizations so that I can manage team workspaces.\",\n      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n        \"Organization plugin added to lib/auth.ts with roles: owner, admin, member\",\n        \"organizationClient() plugin added to lib/auth-client.ts\",\n        \"Organization tables generated and migrated (organization, member, invitation)\",\n        \"\\u003cOrganizationSwitcher /\\u003e from better-auth-ui replaces custom org-switcher.tsx (or rebuilt with better-auth data)\",\n        \"/dashboard/workspaces page uses better-auth-ui org components instead of Clerk's \\u003cOrganizationList\\u003e\",\n        \"/dashboard/workspaces/team page uses better-auth-ui \\u003cOrganizationSettingsCards\\u003e + \\u003cOrganizationMembersCard\\u003e instead of Clerk's \\u003cOrganizationProfile\\u003e\",\n        \"Users can create, switch, and manage organizations\",\n        \"Typecheck passes\"\n      ],\n      \"priority\": 6,\n      \"passes\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"US-007\",\n      \"title\": \"Replace RBAC and nav filtering\",\n      \"description\": \"As a developer, I need role-based access control so that navigation items and pages are restricted by role, permission, and plan.\",\n      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n        \"createAccessControl() configured with statements matching current permissions (e.g., org:teams:manage)\",\n        \"Roles defined: owner, admin, member (matching current Clerk roles)\",\n        \"use-nav.ts hook updated: replace useOrganization() and useUser() from Clerk with better-auth equivalents (authClient.useActiveOrganization(), authClient.useSession())\",\n        \"requireOrg check uses better-auth active organization state\",\n        \"permission check uses authClient.organization.hasPermission()\",\n        \"role check uses active member role from better-auth\",\n        \"plan check uses subscription data from better-auth stripe plugin\",\n        \"/dashboard/exclusive page uses better-auth permission check instead of Clerk's \\u003cProtect\\u003e\",\n        \"Nav items still filter correctly based on org, role, and plan\",\n        \"Typecheck passes\"\n      ],\n      \"priority\": 7,\n      \"passes\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"US-008\",\n      \"title\": \"Add Stripe billing plugin and replace billing page\",\n      \"description\": \"As a user, I want to manage my organization's subscription plan so that I can access premium features.\",\n      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n        \"@better-auth/stripe installed and configured in lib/auth.ts with Stripe client and webhook secret\",\n        \"stripeClient() plugin added to lib/auth-client.ts\",\n        \"Subscription plans defined (matching current Pro/Free tiers)\",\n        \"Webhook route configured (auto-handled by better-auth at /api/auth/stripe/webhook)\",\n        \"/dashboard/billing page rebuilt with custom shadcn UI showing plans and subscription status (replaces Clerk's \\u003cPricingTable\\u003e)\",\n        \"Users can subscribe, upgrade, cancel via Stripe Checkout\",\n        \"Subscription status accessible for RBAC plan checks\",\n        \"Environment variables added: STRIPE_SECRET_KEY, STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET, plan price IDs\",\n        \"Typecheck passes\"\n      ],\n      \"priority\": 8,\n      \"passes\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"US-009\",\n      \"title\": \"Replace user profile/settings page\",\n      \"description\": \"As a user, I want to manage my account settings (name, email, password) from the dashboard.\",\n      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n        \"/dashboard/profile page uses \\u003cAccountSettingsCards /\\u003e and \\u003cSecuritySettingsCards /\\u003e from better-auth-ui instead of Clerk's \\u003cUserProfile\\u003e\",\n        \"User can update name and avatar\",\n        \"User can change password\",\n        \"Typecheck passes\"\n      ],\n      \"priority\": 9,\n      \"passes\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"US-010\",\n      \"title\": \"Remove all Clerk dependencies and clean up\",\n      \"description\": \"As a developer, I want all Clerk code fully removed so there are no dead imports, unused packages, or stale config.\",\n      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n        \"@clerk/nextjs and @clerk/themes uninstalled from package.json\",\n        \"Zero imports from @clerk/* anywhere in the codebase (verified via grep)\",\n        \"Clerk environment variables removed from env.example.txt\",\n        \"docs/clerk_setup.md removed or replaced with docs/auth_setup.md for better-auth\",\n        \"docs/nav-rbac.md updated to reference better-auth instead of Clerk\",\n        \"CLAUDE.md and AGENTS.md updated to reference better-auth\",\n        \"PermissionCheck type in src/types/index.ts updated if needed\",\n        \"App builds successfully (next build)\",\n        \"Typecheck passes\",\n        \"No runtime errors on sign-in, sign-up, dashboard, org switching, billing, profile pages\"\n      ],\n      \"priority\": 10,\n      \"passes\": false\n    }\n  ]\n}","numLines":172,"startLine":1,"totalLines":172}}}
