{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01A9SGJHREyhvChYzY9MUycn","type":"tool_result","content":"# Better Auth UI Requirements\n\nBased on the documentation, here are the prerequisites for using `@daveyplate/better-auth-ui`:\n\n## Required Dependencies\n\n1. **shadcn/ui** - Must be installed with CSS variables enabled\n2. **Sonner** - Configure a `<Toaster />` component for toast notifications\n3. **TailwindCSS** - Version 4 or later, properly set up and configured\n4. **better-auth** - Version 1.3 or greater installed and configured\n\n## Summary\n\nThe library requires a modern React setup with a complete UI component system (shadcn/ui), CSS utility framework (TailwindCSS v4), notification handling (Sonner), and the underlying authentication library (better-auth v1.3+). No specific better-auth plugins are mentioned in the requirements section—only the core library version requirement is specified."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b1ad336c-66a2-4f3f-98dd-2e5d8c4f5736","uuid":"9bd60caf-772a-44a5-bd38-dc0c82cb78bb","tool_use_result":{"bytes":106591,"code":200,"codeText":"OK","result":"# Better Auth UI Requirements\n\nBased on the documentation, here are the prerequisites for using `@daveyplate/better-auth-ui`:\n\n## Required Dependencies\n\n1. **shadcn/ui** - Must be installed with CSS variables enabled\n2. **Sonner** - Configure a `<Toaster />` component for toast notifications\n3. **TailwindCSS** - Version 4 or later, properly set up and configured\n4. **better-auth** - Version 1.3 or greater installed and configured\n\n## Summary\n\nThe library requires a modern React setup with a complete UI component system (shadcn/ui), CSS utility framework (TailwindCSS v4), notification handling (Sonner), and the underlying authentication library (better-auth v1.3+). No specific better-auth plugins are mentioned in the requirements section—only the core library version requirement is specified.","durationMs":3465,"url":"https://better-auth-ui.com/getting-started/requirements"}}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01PSZGUEJFk9u1KEHJ7xfScQ","type":"tool_result","content":"# Better Auth UI Installation Guide\n\n## Package Installation\n\nInstall the library using your preferred package manager:\n\n```bash\nnpm install @daveyplate/better-auth-ui@latest\n```\n\nAlternative options:\n- **pnpm**: `pnpm add @daveyplate/better-auth-ui@latest`\n- **yarn**: `yarn add @daveyplate/better-auth-ui@latest`\n- **bun**: `bun add @daveyplate/better-auth-ui@latest`\n\n## TailwindCSS Configuration\n\n### For TailwindCSS v4\nAdd this import statement to your global CSS file:\n\n```css\n@import \"@daveyplate/better-auth-ui/css\";\n```\n\n### For TailwindCSS v3 (Deprecated)\nUpdate your `tailwind.config` with:\n\n```javascript\ncontent: [\n  \"./node_modules/@daveyplate/better-auth-ui/dist/**/*.{js,ts,jsx,tsx,mdx}\"\n]\n```\n\n## Framework Integration\n\nAfter completing the installation, proceed with one of these framework-specific guides:\n\n- **Next.js** — `/integrations/next-js`\n- **TanStack Start** — `/integrations/tanstack-start`\n- **React** — `/integrations/react`\n\nThe documentation provided does not include detailed AuthUIProvider prop specifications or complete Next.js configuration. Consult the framework-specific integration guides for those details."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b1ad336c-66a2-4f3f-98dd-2e5d8c4f5736","uuid":"f091a2ec-6acd-432a-b0b8-b8654b9d9ab3","tool_use_result":{"bytes":150775,"code":200,"codeText":"OK","result":"# Better Auth UI Installation Guide\n\n## Package Installation\n\nInstall the library using your preferred package manager:\n\n```bash\nnpm install @daveyplate/better-auth-ui@latest\n```\n\nAlternative options:\n- **pnpm**: `pnpm add @daveyplate/better-auth-ui@latest`\n- **yarn**: `yarn add @daveyplate/better-auth-ui@latest`\n- **bun**: `bun add @daveyplate/better-auth-ui@latest`\n\n## TailwindCSS Configuration\n\n### For TailwindCSS v4\nAdd this import statement to your global CSS file:\n\n```css\n@import \"@daveyplate/better-auth-ui/css\";\n```\n\n### For TailwindCSS v3 (Deprecated)\nUpdate your `tailwind.config` with:\n\n```javascript\ncontent: [\n  \"./node_modules/@daveyplate/better-auth-ui/dist/**/*.{js,ts,jsx,tsx,mdx}\"\n]\n```\n\n## Framework Integration\n\nAfter completing the installation, proceed with one of these framework-specific guides:\n\n- **Next.js** — `/integrations/next-js`\n- **TanStack Start** — `/integrations/tanstack-start`\n- **React** — `/integrations/react`\n\nThe documentation provided does not include detailed AuthUIProvider prop specifications or complete Next.js configuration. Consult the framework-specific integration guides for those details.","durationMs":4936,"url":"https://better-auth-ui.com/getting-started/installation"}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01TkrZNs4YYgKZwpnU5cugmD","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_018dVYUFXpob321kZEfp8Qk2","name":"WebFetch","input":{"url":"https://better-auth-ui.com/integrations/next-js","prompt":"Extract the COMPLETE Next.js integration guide for better-auth-ui. Include: AuthUIProvider setup with ALL props (authClient, navigate, replace, onSessionChange, Link, etc.), where to place it in the component tree, any routing configuration, and complete code examples."},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":226,"cache_creation_input_tokens":586,"cache_read_input_tokens":74279,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":586},"output_tokens":20,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b1ad336c-66a2-4f3f-98dd-2e5d8c4f5736","uuid":"07fd2437-22a9-4e63-a09b-50bcd4df783a"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_018dVYUFXpob321kZEfp8Qk2","type":"tool_result","content":"# Next.js Integration Guide for Better Auth UI\n\n## AuthUIProvider Setup\n\nThe `AuthUIProvider` is a client component that must wrap your layout to provide authentication context across your application.\n\n### Required Props\n\n**Core Props:**\n- `authClient`: Your Better Auth client instance\n- `navigate`: Router push function (e.g., `router.push`)\n- `replace`: Router replace function (e.g., `router.replace`)\n- `Link`: Next.js Link component for navigation\n- `onSessionChange`: Callback fired when auth state changes\n\n### App Router Implementation\n\n**File: `app/providers.tsx`**\n\n```typescript\n\"use client\"\n\nimport { AuthUIProvider } from \"@daveyplate/better-auth-ui\"\nimport Link from \"next/link\"\nimport { useRouter } from \"next/navigation\"\nimport type { ReactNode } from \"react\"\nimport { authClient } from \"@/lib/auth-client\"\n\nexport function Providers({ children }: { children: ReactNode }) {\n    const router = useRouter()\n\n    return (\n        <AuthUIProvider\n            authClient={authClient}\n            navigate={router.push}\n            replace={router.replace}\n            onSessionChange={() => {\n                router.refresh()\n            }}\n            Link={Link}\n        >\n            {children}\n        </AuthUIProvider>\n    )\n}\n```\n\n**File: `app/layout.tsx`**\n\n```typescript\nimport type { ReactNode } from \"react\"\nimport { Providers } from \"./providers\"\n\nexport default function RootLayout({ children }: { children: ReactNode }) {\n    return (\n        <html lang=\"en\">\n            <body>\n                <Providers>{children}</Providers>\n            </body>\n        </html>\n    )\n}\n```\n\n### Critical Note on Session Changes\n\n\"Since the Next.js App Router caches routes by default, navigation to protected routes may fail until you perform a `router.refresh()` to clear the cache.\" The `onSessionChange` callback must invoke `router.refresh()` to clear cached content when authentication state updates.\n\n## Route Configuration\n\n### Auth Routes (`app/auth/[path]/page.tsx`)\n\n```typescript\nimport { AuthView } from \"@daveyplate/better-auth-ui\"\nimport { authViewPaths } from \"@daveyplate/better-auth-ui/server\"\n\nexport const dynamicParams = false\n\nexport function generateStaticParams() {\n    return Object.values(authViewPaths).map((path) => ({ path }))\n}\n\nexport default async function AuthPage({ params }: { params: Promise<{ path: string }> }) {\n    const { path } = await params\n    return (\n        <main className=\"container flex grow flex-col items-center justify-center self-center p-4 md:p-6\">\n            <AuthView path={path} />\n        </main>\n    )\n}\n```\n\n**Available paths:** `/auth/sign-in`, `/auth/sign-up`, `/auth/magic-link`, `/auth/forgot-password`, `/auth/two-factor`, `/auth/recover-account`, `/auth/reset-password`, `/auth/sign-out`, `/auth/callback`, `/auth/accept-invitation`\n\n### Account Routes (`app/account/[path]/page.tsx`)\n\nSimilar structure using `AccountView` and `accountViewPaths` from the library.\n\n### Organization Routes with Slugs\n\nFor slug-based URLs (e.g., `/organization/my-org/settings`), update `AuthUIProvider`:\n\n```typescript\n<AuthUIProvider\n    organization={{\n        pathMode: \"slug\",\n        basePath: \"/organization\",\n        slug // from useParams()\n    }}\n    // ... other props\n/>\n```\n\nThen create nested route: `app/organization/[slug]/[path]/page.tsx`\n\n## Pages Router Implementation\n\n**File: `pages/_app.tsx`**\n\n```typescript\nimport type { AppProps } from \"next/app\"\nimport { AuthUIProvider } from \"@daveyplate/better-auth-ui\"\nimport { useRouter } from \"next/router\"\nimport Link from \"next/link\"\nimport { authClient } from \"@/lib/auth-client\"\n\nexport default function App({ Component, pageProps }: AppProps) {\n    const router = useRouter()\n\n    return (\n        <AuthUIProvider\n            authClient={authClient}\n            navigate={router.push}\n            replace={router.replace}\n            Link={Link}\n        >\n            <Component {...pageProps} />\n        </AuthUIProvider>\n    )\n}\n```\n\nThe `AuthUIProvider` can be customized with \"plugins, styles, localization and more\" via additional configuration options documented in the component reference."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b1ad336c-66a2-4f3f-98dd-2e5d8c4f5736","uuid":"71d39421-fc4a-4b2c-8a75-59e95edaa9f7","tool_use_result":{"bytes":463231,"code":200,"codeText":"OK","result":"# Next.js Integration Guide for Better Auth UI\n\n## AuthUIProvider Setup\n\nThe `AuthUIProvider` is a client component that must wrap your layout to provide authentication context across your application.\n\n### Required Props\n\n**Core Props:**\n- `authClient`: Your Better Auth client instance\n- `navigate`: Router push function (e.g., `router.push`)\n- `replace`: Router replace function (e.g., `router.replace`)\n- `Link`: Next.js Link component for navigation\n- `onSessionChange`: Callback fired when auth state changes\n\n### App Router Implementation\n\n**File: `app/providers.tsx`**\n\n```typescript\n\"use client\"\n\nimport { AuthUIProvider } from \"@daveyplate/better-auth-ui\"\nimport Link from \"next/link\"\nimport { useRouter } from \"next/navigation\"\nimport type { ReactNode } from \"react\"\nimport { authClient } from \"@/lib/auth-client\"\n\nexport function Providers({ children }: { children: ReactNode }) {\n    const router = useRouter()\n\n    return (\n        <AuthUIProvider\n            authClient={authClient}\n            navigate={router.push}\n            replace={router.replace}\n            onSessionChange={() => {\n                router.refresh()\n            }}\n            Link={Link}\n        >\n            {children}\n        </AuthUIProvider>\n    )\n}\n```\n\n**File: `app/layout.tsx`**\n\n```typescript\nimport type { ReactNode } from \"react\"\nimport { Providers } from \"./providers\"\n\nexport default function RootLayout({ children }: { children: ReactNode }) {\n    return (\n        <html lang=\"en\">\n            <body>\n                <Providers>{children}</Providers>\n            </body>\n        </html>\n    )\n}\n```\n\n### Critical Note on Session Changes\n\n\"Since the Next.js App Router caches routes by default, navigation to protected routes may fail until you perform a `router.refresh()` to clear the cache.\" The `onSessionChange` callback must invoke `router.refresh()` to clear cached content when authentication state updates.\n\n## Route Configuration\n\n### Auth Routes (`app/auth/[path]/page.tsx`)\n\n```typescript\nimport { AuthView } from \"@daveyplate/better-auth-ui\"\nimport { authViewPaths } from \"@daveyplate/better-auth-ui/server\"\n\nexport const dynamicParams = false\n\nexport function generateStaticParams() {\n    return Object.values(authViewPaths).map((path) => ({ path }))\n}\n\nexport default async function AuthPage({ params }: { params: Promise<{ path: string }> }) {\n    const { path } = await params\n    return (\n        <main className=\"container flex grow flex-col items-center justify-center self-center p-4 md:p-6\">\n            <AuthView path={path} />\n        </main>\n    )\n}\n```\n\n**Available paths:** `/auth/sign-in`, `/auth/sign-up`, `/auth/magic-link`, `/auth/forgot-password`, `/auth/two-factor`, `/auth/recover-account`, `/auth/reset-password`, `/auth/sign-out`, `/auth/callback`, `/auth/accept-invitation`\n\n### Account Routes (`app/account/[path]/page.tsx`)\n\nSimilar structure using `AccountView` and `accountViewPaths` from the library.\n\n### Organization Routes with Slugs\n\nFor slug-based URLs (e.g., `/organization/my-org/settings`), update `AuthUIProvider`:\n\n```typescript\n<AuthUIProvider\n    organization={{\n        pathMode: \"slug\",\n        basePath: \"/organization\",\n        slug // from useParams()\n    }}\n    // ... other props\n/>\n```\n\nThen create nested route: `app/organization/[slug]/[path]/page.tsx`\n\n## Pages Router Implementation\n\n**File: `pages/_app.tsx`**\n\n```typescript\nimport type { AppProps } from \"next/app\"\nimport { AuthUIProvider } from \"@daveyplate/better-auth-ui\"\nimport { useRouter } from \"next/router\"\nimport Link from \"next/link\"\nimport { authClient } from \"@/lib/auth-client\"\n\nexport default function App({ Component, pageProps }: AppProps) {\n    const router = useRouter()\n\n    return (\n        <AuthUIProvider\n            authClient={authClient}\n            navigate={router.push}\n            replace={router.replace}\n            Link={Link}\n        >\n            <Component {...pageProps} />\n        </AuthUIProvider>\n    )\n}\n```\n\nThe `AuthUIProvider` can be customized with \"plugins, styles, localization and more\" via additional configuration options documented in the component reference.","durationMs":9826,"url":"https://better-auth-ui.com/integrations/next-js"}}
