{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01Qo99WpwCs3n3rKD5ErEnsj","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I see how it works. Line 15 is key:\n\n```typescript\ntype InferResolvedHooks<O extends BetterAuthClientOptions> = O extends {\n  plugins: Array<infer Plugin>;\n} ? UnionToIntersection<Plugin extends BetterAuthClientPlugin ? Plugin[\"getAtoms\"] extends ((fetch: any) => infer Atoms) ? Atoms extends Record<string, any> ? { [key in keyof Atoms as IsSignal<key> extends true ? never : key extends string ? `use${Capitalize<key>}` : never]: () => ReturnType<Atoms[key][\"get\"]> } : {} : {} : {}> : {};\n\n\n```\n\nIt extracts atom names from the plugin's `getAtoms` and transforms them into hooks with the `use` prefix. So `activeOrganization` becomes `useActiveOrganization`, `listOrganizations` becomes `useListOrganizations`, and so on. The return type pulls directly from each atom's `get` method, which for `AuthQueryAtom` gives you the data type itself. I'm trying to understand how this maps to what `useSession` actually returns.\n\n```","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2325,"cache_read_input_tokens":49817,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2325},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"5446c01b-aad1-4950-90be-ff6f7dc92b2d","uuid":"d7fb1e47-dc4e-48a7-b3e4-67a8ec1159a2"}
