{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01BjXzenejXARHrekEGCSrb3","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So `AuthQueryAtom<T>` has a `get()` that returns `{ data: null | T, error, isPending, isRefetching, refetch }`. And the React hooks created from atoms return `ReturnType<Atoms[key][\"get\"]>`.\n\nSo `authClient.useActiveMember()` returns `{ data: null | { id: string, organizationId: string, userId: string, role: string, createdAt: Date }, error, isPending, isRefetching, refetch }`.\n\nSo my code using `const { data: activeMember } = authClient.useActiveMember()` should work.\n\n\nLet me verify the types actually check out with the plugin setup I'm using.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":504,"cache_read_input_tokens":52961,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":504},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"5446c01b-aad1-4950-90be-ff6f7dc92b2d","uuid":"aad5d779-f220-4fdb-85b2-30897fcfe73d"}
