{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01UZ6tjQSpNHbXq6M1gCnNZm","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Simplified Navigation RBAC System\n     2→\n     3→## Overview\n     4→\n     5→This document explains the fully client-side RBAC (Role-Based Access Control) system for navigation items.\n     6→\n     7→**Key Insight**: Navigation visibility is UX only, not security. We can check everything client-side using Clerk's hooks!\n     8→\n     9→## Architecture\n    10→\n    11→### Core Files\n    12→\n    13→1. **`src/hooks/use-nav.ts`** - Single hook that handles all filtering logic (fully client-side)\n    14→2. **`src/types/index.ts`** - Type definitions with `access` property\n    15→\n    16→### Why Client-Side?\n    17→\n    18→- **Navigation visibility is UX only** - Users can't bypass security by seeing/hiding nav items\n    19→- **Clerk provides all data client-side** - `useOrganization()` gives us `membership.permissions` and `membership.role`\n    20→- **Zero server calls** - Instant filtering, no loading states, no UI flashing\n    21→- **Better performance** - No network latency, no async complexity\n    22→\n    23→**Note**: For actual security (API routes, server actions, page protection), always use server-side checks.\n    24→\n    25→## Performance Characteristics\n    26→\n    27→### All Checks Are Synchronous\n    28→\n    29→✅ **requireOrg**: Client-side check using `useOrganization()`  \n    30→✅ **permission**: Client-side check using `membership.permissions` array  \n    31→✅ **role**: Client-side check using `membership.role`  \n    32→⚠️ **plan/feature**: Requires server-side check (see below)\n    33→\n    34→### Zero Server Calls\n    35→\n    36→- All navigation filtering happens synchronously\n    37→- No loading states\n    38→- No UI flashing\n    39→- Instant results\n    40→\n    41→## Usage\n    42→\n    43→### In `nav-config.ts`\n    44→\n    45→```typescript\n    46→{\n    47→  title: 'Teams',\n    48→  url: '/dashboard/workspaces/team',\n    49→  icon: 'userPen',\n    50→  // Simple: requireOrg (client-side check, instant)\n    51→  access: { requireOrg: true }\n    52→}\n    53→\n    54→{\n    55→  title: 'Admin Panel',\n    56→  url: '/dashboard/admin',\n    57→  icon: 'settings',\n    58→  // All client-side checks - instant!\n    59→  access: {\n    60→    requireOrg: true,\n    61→    permission: 'org:admin:manage',  // Client-side from membership.permissions\n    62→    role: 'admin'  // Client-side from membership.role\n    63→}\n    64→```\n    65→\n    66→### In Components\n    67→\n    68→```typescript\n    69→import { useFilteredNavItems } from '@/hooks/use-nav';\n    70→\n    71→function MyComponent() {\n    72→  const filteredItems = useFilteredNavItems(navItems);\n    73→  // filteredItems is automatically filtered based on RBAC\n    74→}\n    75→```\n    76→\n    77→### Plan/Feature Checks\n    78→\n    79→Plans and features require Clerk's `has()` function which is server-side only. Options:\n    80→\n    81→1. **Store in organization metadata** (recommended for navigation):\n    82→\n    83→   ```typescript\n    84→   // In your organization setup\n    85→   organization.publicMetadata.plan = 'pro';\n    86→\n    87→   // In nav-config.ts\n    88→   access: {\n    89→     requireOrg: true,\n    90→     // Check metadata instead of plan\n    91→   }\n    92→   ```\n    93→\n    94→2. **Show item, protect at page level** (current approach):\n    95→   - Navigation item is shown\n    96→   - Page component checks server-side and redirects/shows error if needed\n    97→\n    98→3. **Use server action** (if you really need it):\n    99→   - Only for navigation items that absolutely need plan/feature checks\n   100→   - Most navigation items won't need this\n   101→\n   102→## Scalability\n   103→\n   104→### Adding New Items\n   105→\n   106→Just add to `nav-config.ts`:\n   107→\n   108→```typescript\n   109→{\n   110→  title: 'New Feature',\n   111→  url: '/dashboard/new',\n   112→  icon: 'star',\n   113→  access: { plan: 'pro' }  // That's it!\n   114→}\n   115→```\n   116→\n   117→The system automatically:\n   118→\n   119→- Filters it in sidebar\n   120→- Filters it in kbar\n   121→- Handles async checks if needed\n   122→- Handles sync checks immediately\n   123→\n   124→### Adding New Access Types\n   125→\n   126→1. Add to `PermissionCheck` interface in `src/app/actions/rbac.ts`\n   127→2. Add check logic in `checkAccess()` function\n   128→3. Update `use-nav.ts` to handle the new type\n   129→\n   130→## Comparison: Before vs After\n   131→\n   132→### Before (Overcomplicated)\n   133→\n   134→- 4 files with complex logic\n   135→- Multiple hooks and utilities\n   136→- Unclear data flow\n   137→- Potential for bugs\n   138→\n   139→### After (Simplified)\n   140→\n   141→- 1 main hook file\n   142→- Clear, linear logic\n   143→- Easy to understand\n   144→- Easy to maintain\n   145→\n   146→## Best Practices\n   147→\n   148→1. **Use `requireOrg: true` for simple cases** - It's instant and requires no server call\n   149→2. **Combine checks when possible** - `{ requireOrg: true, permission: '...' }` is more efficient than separate checks\n   150→3. **Avoid unnecessary checks** - Don't add `access` if the item should always be visible\n   151→\n   152→## Migration from Old System\n   153→\n   154→The old `visible` function still works for backward compatibility:\n   155→\n   156→```typescript\n   157→// Old way (still works)\n   158→visible: (context) => !!context?.organization;\n   159→\n   160→// New way (recommended)\n   161→access: {\n   162→  requireOrg: true;\n   163→}\n   164→```\n   165→\n   166→## Future Improvements\n   167→\n   168→Potential optimizations if needed:\n   169→\n   170→1. Cache permission checks (e.g., React Query)\n   171→2. Prefetch permissions on app load\n   172→3. Optimistic UI updates\n   173→\n   174→But for now, the current implementation is:\n   175→\n   176→- ✅ Simple\n   177→- ✅ Fast\n   178→- ✅ Scalable\n   179→- ✅ Maintainable\n   180→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01MCDjZVQ9znYCyrVzkSMb8F","session_id":"5ecfe1e9-6f52-4d05-b142-586fa1064d01","uuid":"0a3c898f-41a0-4662-8749-816e0cf4ed89"}
