{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01MCDjZVQ9znYCyrVzkSMb8F","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information. Let me create a comprehensive summary of the current billing page, auth config, and related files:\n\n## Summary: Current Billing & Auth Configuration\n\nI've completed a thorough analysis of your codebase. Here's what I found:\n\n---\n\n### 1. **Current Billing Page** (`/src/app/dashboard/billing/page.tsx`)\n\n**Status**: Uses Clerk's `<PricingTable>` component (client-side)\n\n**Key characteristics**:\n- Checks for active organization using `useOrganization()` from `@clerk/nextjs`\n- Shows \"No Organization Selected\" fallback if no org exists\n- Renders `<PricingTable for='organization' />` from Clerk\n- Uses `PageContainer` with `billingInfoContent` from infoconfig\n- Currently no Stripe integration (Clerk handles it)\n\n**What needs to be replaced for better-auth + Stripe**:\n- Remove `useOrganization()` hook\n- Build custom shadcn/ui pricing/billing components\n- Integrate with Stripe API via better-auth stripe plugin\n- Fetch plans and subscription status from better-auth database\n\n---\n\n### 2. **Server Auth Config** (`/src/lib/auth.ts`)\n\n**Current setup**:\n```typescript\nimport { betterAuth } from 'better-auth';\nimport { drizzleAdapter } from 'better-auth/adapters/drizzle';\nimport { nextCookies } from 'better-auth/next-js';\nimport { organization } from 'better-auth/plugins';\nimport { db } from './db';\n\nexport const auth = betterAuth({\n  database: drizzleAdapter(db, {\n    provider: 'sqlite'\n  }),\n  emailAndPassword: {\n    enabled: true\n  },\n  plugins: [\n    nextCookies(),\n    organization({\n      allowUserToCreateOrganization: true,\n      creatorRole: 'owner'\n    })\n  ]\n});\n```\n\n**To add Stripe plugin**, you'll need to add:\n- `import { stripe } from 'better-auth/plugins'`\n- Add stripe plugin to the plugins array with Stripe keys\n- Configure webhook secret for payment processing\n\n---\n\n### 3. **Client Auth Config** (`/src/lib/auth-client.ts`)\n\n**Current setup**:\n```typescript\nimport { createAuthClient } from 'better-auth/react';\nimport { organizationClient } from 'better-auth/client/plugins';\n\nexport const authClient = createAuthClient({\n  plugins: [organizationClient()]\n});\n```\n\n**To add Stripe plugin**, you'll need to:\n- Import `stripeClient` from `'better-auth/client/plugins'`\n- Add to plugins array\n\n---\n\n### 4. **Environment Variables** (`env.example.txt`)\n\n**Current Clerk/better-auth vars**:\n```\nNEXT_PUBLIC_CLERK_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=\nCLERK_SECRET_KEY=\nNEXT_PUBLIC_CLERK_SIGN_IN_URL=\"/auth/sign-in\"\nNEXT_PUBLIC_CLERK_SIGN_UP_URL=\"/auth/sign-up\"\nNEXT_PUBLIC_CLERK_AFTER_SIGN_IN_URL=\"/dashboard/overview\"\nNEXT_PUBLIC_CLERK_AFTER_SIGN_UP_URL=\"/dashboard/overview\"\n\nBETTER_AUTH_SECRET=\nBETTER_AUTH_URL=http://localhost:3000\nDATABASE_PATH=./sqlite.db\n```\n\n**Need to add for Stripe**:\n- `STRIPE_SECRET_KEY` (private)\n- `NEXT_PUBLIC_STRIPE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY` (public)\n- `STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET` (for webhook validation)\n\n---\n\n### 5. **Database Schema** (`/src/lib/auth-schema.ts`)\n\n**Current tables** (via better-auth):\n- `user`, `session`, `account`, `verification`\n- `organization`, `member`, `invitation`\n\n**Note**: The stripe plugin will auto-create:\n- `subscription` table (tracks org-level subscriptions)\n- `stripeCustomer` table (maps orgs to Stripe customer IDs)\n\nThe schema file is already set up with Drizzle ORM and uses SQLite.\n\n---\n\n### 6. **Package.json**\n\n**Current dependencies**:\n- `better-auth@^1.5.6` ✓ (already installed)\n- `@daveyplate/better-auth-ui@^3.4.0` ✓ (UI components)\n- `drizzle-orm@^0.45.2` ✓\n- `better-sqlite3@^12.8.0` ✓\n- `@clerk/nextjs@^6.39.1` (to be removed in future PRs)\n\n**Need to add for Stripe**:\n- `@better-auth/stripe` (Stripe plugin for better-auth)\n- `stripe` (Stripe client library)\n\n---\n\n### 7. **Existing Stripe References**\n\n**Found in codebase**:\n- `/src/app/dashboard/exclusive/page.tsx` (line 13): `// Plan check placeholder — actual subscription check will use stripe plugin (US-008)`\n- `/src/hooks/use-nav.ts` (line 101): `// Plan/feature checks require stripe plugin (US-008)`\n\n**What's already in place**:\n- Navigation RBAC system supports `plan` and `feature` checks in `PermissionCheck` interface\n- Exclusive page shows placeholder for Pro plan access control\n- `use-nav.ts` already warns about plan/feature checks needing server-side verification\n\n---\n\n### 8. **RBAC & Navigation System** \n\n**Current implementation**:\n- `/src/hooks/use-nav.ts` - Fully client-side filtering\n- `/src/config/nav-config.ts` - Navigation items with `access` property\n- Supports: `requireOrg`, `permission`, `role`, `plan` (stub), `feature` (stub)\n- Billing nav item requires organization: `access: { requireOrg: true }`\n- Exclusive page currently shows if organization exists (placeholder)\n\n**For Stripe integration**, you'll need:\n- Server action or endpoint to check subscription status\n- Database lookup in `subscription` table created by stripe plugin\n\n---\n\n### 9. **API Route for better-auth**\n\n**Current**: `/src/app/api/auth/[...all]/route.ts`\n```typescript\nimport { auth } from '@/lib/auth';\nimport { toNextJsHandler } from 'better-auth/next-js';\n\nexport const { POST, GET } = toNextJsHandler(auth);\n```\n\n**For Stripe**: better-auth automatically adds webhook route at `/api/auth/stripe/webhook` once plugin is configured.\n\n---\n\n### 10. **Key Files to Read/Understand**\n\n**Absolute paths**:\n1. `/Users/bogdantarasenko/Desktop/hackinterview-tool/next-shadcn-dashboard-starter/src/app/dashboard/billing/page.tsx`\n2. `/Users/bogdantarasenko/Desktop/hackinterview-tool/next-shadcn-dashboard-starter/src/lib/auth.ts`\n3. `/Users/bogdantarasenko/Desktop/hackinterview-tool/next-shadcn-dashboard-starter/src/lib/auth-client.ts`\n4. `/Users/bogdantarasenko/Desktop/hackinterview-tool/next-shadcn-dashboard-starter/src/lib/auth-schema.ts` (database)\n5. `/Users/bogdantarasenko/Desktop/hackinterview-tool/next-shadcn-dashboard-starter/env.example.txt`\n6. `/Users/bogdantarasenko/Desktop/hackinterview-tool/next-shadcn-dashboard-starter/package.json`\n7. `/Users/bogdantarasenko/Desktop/hackinterview-tool/next-shadcn-dashboard-starter/src/hooks/use-nav.ts` (RBAC filtering)\n8. `/Users/bogdantarasenko/Desktop/hackinterview-tool/next-shadcn-dashboard-starter/src/config/nav-config.ts` (navigation config)\n9. `/Users/bogdantarasenko/Desktop/hackinterview-tool/next-shadcn-dashboard-starter/src/config/infoconfig.ts` (billing info content)\n10. `/Users/bogdantarasenko/Desktop/hackinterview-tool/next-shadcn-dashboard-starter/.chief/prds/main/prd.md` (US-008 requirements)\n\n---\n\n### 11. **Summary for US-008 Implementation**\n\n**What currently exists**:\n- better-auth is fully configured with organizations\n- SQLite database with Drizzle ORM\n- RBAC system with navigation filtering\n- Placeholder billing page using Clerk\n\n**What needs to be built**:\n1. Install `@better-auth/stripe` and `stripe`\n2. Add Stripe plugin to `src/lib/auth.ts`\n3. Add Stripe client plugin to `src/lib/auth-client.ts`\n4. Add Stripe environment variables\n5. Build custom billing page with plans and checkout\n6. Implement subscription status checking in `use-nav.ts` for plan/feature access\n7. Wire up Stripe webhook handling (auto-handled by better-auth)\n\n**No other Stripe code exists yet** - this is a clean slate for the integration."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a67872c519660a20f (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 83949\ntool_uses: 42\nduration_ms: 75680</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"5ecfe1e9-6f52-4d05-b142-586fa1064d01","uuid":"7e6cf2b3-5d4d-4956-897d-596884221ee8","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"I need to understand the current billing page, auth config, and related files fo