{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01GBiLWxyG1A63sRv9sv8Gwv","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# =================================================================\n     2→# Authentication Configuration (Clerk)\n     3→# =================================================================\n     4→# IMPORTANT: This template supports Clerk's keyless mode!\n     5→# You can start using the app immediately without any configuration.\n     6→# When you're ready to claim your application, simply click the Clerk\n     7→# popup at the bottom of the screen to get your API keys.\n     8→\n     9→# Required: Clerk API Keys (Leave empty for keyless mode)\n    10→\n    11→NEXT_PUBLIC_CLERK_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=\n    12→CLERK_SECRET_KEY=\n    13→\n    14→\n    15→# Authentication Redirect URLs\n    16→# These control where users are directed after authentication actions\n    17→\n    18→NEXT_PUBLIC_CLERK_SIGN_IN_URL=\"/auth/sign-in\"\n    19→NEXT_PUBLIC_CLERK_SIGN_UP_URL=\"/auth/sign-up\"\n    20→NEXT_PUBLIC_CLERK_AFTER_SIGN_IN_URL=\"/dashboard/overview\"\n    21→NEXT_PUBLIC_CLERK_AFTER_SIGN_UP_URL=\"/dashboard/overview\"\n    22→\n    23→\n    24→# =================================================================\n    25→# Clerk Organizations Configuration\n    26→# =================================================================\n    27→# To enable Organizations in your Clerk Dashboard:\n    28→# 1. Go to https://dashboard.clerk.com\n    29→# 2. Navigate to Organizations Settings\n    30→# 3. Enable \"Organizations\"\n    31→# 4. Configure default roles (admin, member, viewer) if needed\n    32→# 5. Set membership limits (default: 5 members on Free plan)\n    33→#\n    34→# Development Plan Features:\n    35→# - Up to 50 Monthly Active Organizations (MAOs) in development\n    36→# - Up to 5 members per organization on Free plan\n    37→# - Unlimited members on Pro plan\n    38→#\n    39→# For more information, see: https://clerk.com/docs/organizations/overview\n    40→\n    41→\n    42→# =================================================================\n    43→# Clerk Webhooks (Optional - for production billing)\n    44→# =================================================================\n    45→# If you're using Clerk Billing or webhooks, add your webhook secret here.\n    46→# You can find this in Clerk Dashboard > Webhooks\n    47→\n    48→WEBHOOK_SECRET=    # Example: whsec_...\n    49→\n    50→\n    51→# =================================================================\n    52→# Authentication Configuration (Better Auth)\n    53→# =================================================================\n    54→# Better Auth is a self-hosted, TypeScript-first auth library.\n    55→# Generate a secret with: openssl rand -base64 32\n    56→\n    57→BETTER_AUTH_SECRET=    # Required: Auth secret key\n    58→BETTER_AUTH_URL=http://localhost:3000    # Base URL of your app\n    59→\n    60→# Database path (SQLite)\n    61→DATABASE_PATH=./sqlite.db\n    62→\n    63→\n    64→# =================================================================\n    65→# Build Configuration\n    66→# =================================================================\n    67→# Set to 'true' when deploying with Docker or self-hosting on a VPS.\n    68→# This enables Next.js standalone output mode for smaller deployments.\n    69→\n    70→BUILD_STANDALONE=    # Example: \"true\"\n    71→\n    72→\n    73→# =================================================================\n    74→# Error Tracking Configuration (Sentry)\n    75→# =================================================================\n    76→# To set up Sentry error tracking:\n    77→# 1. Create an account at https://sentry.io\n    78→# 2. Create a new project for Next.js\n    79→# 3. Follow the setup instructions below\n    80→\n    81→# Step 1: Sentry DSN (Required)\n    82→# Found at: Settings > Projects > [Your Project] > Client Keys (DSN)\n    83→\n    84→NEXT_PUBLIC_SENTRY_DSN=    #Example: https://****@****.ingest.sentry.io/****\n    85→\n    86→\n    87→# Step 2: Organization & Project Details\n    88→# Found at: Settings > Organization > General Settings\n    89→\n    90→NEXT_PUBLIC_SENTRY_ORG=  # Example: acme-corp\n    91→NEXT_PUBLIC_SENTRY_PROJECT=  # Example: nextjs-dashboard\n    92→\n    93→\n    94→# Step 3: Sentry Auth Token\n    95→\n    96→# Sentry can automatically provide readable stack traces for errors using source maps, requiring a Sentry auth token.\n    97→# More info: https://docs.sentry.io/platforms/javascript/guides/nextjs/manual-setup/#step-4-add-readable-stack-traces-with-source-maps-optional\n    98→\n    99→SENTRY_AUTH_TOKEN=    #Example: sntrys_************************************\n   100→\n   101→\n   102→# Step 4: Environment Control (Optional)\n   103→# Set to 'true' to disable Sentry in development\n   104→\n   105→NEXT_PUBLIC_SENTRY_DISABLED= \"false\"\n   106→\n   107→\n   108→# =================================================================\n   109→# Important Notes:\n   110→# =================================================================\n   111→# 1. Rename this file to '.env' for local development\n   112→# 2. Never commit the actual '.env' file to version control\n   113→# 3. Make sure to replace all placeholder values with real ones\n   114→# 4. Keep your secret keys private and never share them\n   115→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"5ecfe1e9-6f52-4d05-b142-586fa1064d01","uuid":"0405c31d-b128-4389-b750-1d63c9221ffc","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/bogdantarasenko/Desktop/hackinterview-tool/next-shadcn-dashboard-starter/env.example.txt","content":"# =================================================================\n# Authentication Configuration (Clerk)\n# =================================================================\n# IMPORTANT: This template supports Clerk's keyless mode!\n# You can start using the app immediately without any configuration.\n# When you're ready to claim your application, simply click the Clerk\n# popup at the bottom of the screen to get your API keys.\n\n# Required: Clerk API Keys (Leave empty for keyless mode)\n\nNEXT_PUBLIC_CLERK_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=\nCLERK_SECRET_KEY=\n\n\n# Authentication Redirect URLs\n# These control where users are directed after authentication actions\n\nNEXT_PUBLIC_CLERK_SIGN_IN_URL=\"/auth/sign-in\"\nNEXT_PUBLIC_CLERK_SIGN_UP_URL=\"/auth/sign-up\"\nNEXT_PUBLIC_CLERK_AFTER_SIGN_IN_URL=\"/dashboard/overview\"\nNEXT_PUBLIC_CLERK_AFTER_SIGN_UP_URL=\"/dashboard/overview\"\n\n\n# =================================================================\n# Clerk Organizations Configuration\n# =================================================================\n# To enable Organizations in your Clerk Dashboard:\n# 1. Go to https://dashboard.clerk.com\n# 2. Navigate to Organizations Settings\n# 3. Enable \"Organizations\"\n# 4. Configure default roles (admin, member, viewer) if needed\n# 5. Set membership limits (default: 5 members on Free plan)\n#\n# Development Plan Features:\n# - Up to 50 Monthly Active Organizations (MAOs) in development\n# - Up to 5 members per organization on Free plan\n# - Unlimited members on Pro plan\n#\n# For more information, see: https://clerk.com/docs/organizations/overview\n\n\n# =================================================================\n# Clerk Webhooks (Optional - for production billing)\n# =================================================================\n# If you're using Clerk Billing or webhooks, add your webhook secret here.\n# You can find this in Clerk Dashboard > Webhooks\n\nWEBHOOK_SECRET=    # Example: whsec_...\n\n\n# =================================================================\n# Authentication Configuration (Better Auth)\n# =================================================================\n# Better Auth is a self-hosted, TypeScript-first auth library.\n# Generate a secret with: openssl rand -base64 32\n\nBETTER_AUTH_SECRET=    # Required: Auth secret key\nBETTER_AUTH_URL=http://localhost:3000    # Base URL of your app\n\n# Database path (SQLite)\nDATABASE_PATH=./sqlite.db\n\n\n# =================================================================\n# Build Configuration\n# =================================================================\n# Set to 'true' when deploying with Docker or self-hosting on a VPS.\n# This enables Next.js standalone output mode for smaller deployments.\n\nBUILD_STANDALONE=    # Example: \"true\"\n\n\n# =================================================================\n# Error Tracking Configuration (Sentry)\n# =================================================================\n# To set up Sentry error tracking:\n# 1. Create an account at https://sentry.io\n# 2. Create a new project for Next.js\n# 3. Follow the setup instructions below\n\n# Step 1: Sentry DSN (Required)\n# Found at: Settings > Projects > [Your Project] > Client Keys (DSN)\n\nNEXT_PUBLIC_SENTRY_DSN=    #Example: https://****@****.ingest.sentry.io/****\n\n\n# Step 2: Organization & Project Details\n# Found at: Settings > Organization > General Settings\n\nNEXT_PUBLIC_SENTRY_ORG=  # Example: acme-corp\nNEXT_PUBLIC_SENTRY_PROJECT=  # Example: nextjs-dashboard\n\n\n# Step 3: Sentry Auth Token\n\n# Sentry can automatically provide readable stack traces for errors using source maps, requiring a Sentry auth token.\n# More info: https://docs.sentry.io/platforms/javascript/guides/nextjs/manual-setup/#step-4-add-readable-stack-traces-with-source-maps-optional\n\nSENTRY_AUTH_TOKEN=    #Example: sntrys_************************************\n\n\n# Step 4: Environment Control (Optional)\n# Set to 'true' to disable Sentry in development\n\nNEXT_PUBLIC_SENTRY_DISABLED= \"false\"\n\n\n# =================================================================\n# Important Notes:\n# =================================================================\n# 1. Rename this file to '.env' for local development\n# 2. Never commit the actual '.env' file to version control\n# 3. Make sure to replace all placeholder values with real ones\n# 4. Keep your secret keys private and never share them\n","numLines":115,"startLine":1,"totalLines":115}}}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_015885BDgJR86XtaddBT4Gne","type":"tool_result","content":"# Better Auth Stripe Plugin Documentation Extract\n\n## Installation\n\n**Package:** `@better-auth/stripe`\n```bash\nnpm install @better-auth/stripe stripe@^20.0.0\n```\n\n## Server Configuration\n\nAdd to your `auth.ts`:\n\n```typescript\nimport { betterAuth } from \"better-auth\"\nimport { stripe } from \"@better-auth/stripe\"\nimport Stripe from \"stripe\"\n\nconst stripeClient = new Stripe(process.env.STRIPE_SECRET_KEY!)\n\nexport const auth = betterAuth({\n  plugins: [\n    stripe({\n      stripeClient,\n      stripeWebhookSecret: process.env.STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET!,\n      createCustomerOnSignUp: true\n    })\n  ]\n})\n```\n\n## Client Configuration\n\nAdd to your `auth-client.ts`:\n\n```typescript\nimport { createAuthClient } from \"better-auth/client\"\nimport { stripeClient } from \"@better-auth/stripe/client\"\n\nexport const authClient = createAuthClient({\n  plugins: [\n    stripeClient({ subscription: true })\n  ]\n})\n```\n\n## Core Methods\n\n**Upgrade/Create Subscription:**\n```typescript\nawait authClient.subscription.upgrade({\n  plan: \"pro\",\n  annual: true,\n  successUrl: \"/dashboard\",\n  cancelUrl: \"/pricing\",\n  seats: 5\n})\n```\n\n**List Active Subscriptions:**\n```typescript\nconst { data: subscriptions } = await authClient.subscription.list({\n  query: { referenceId: '123', customerType: 'user' }\n})\n```\n\n**Cancel Subscription:**\n```typescript\nawait authClient.subscription.cancel({\n  subscriptionId: 'sub_123',\n  returnUrl: '/account'\n})\n```\n\n**Restore Subscription:**\n```typescript\nawait authClient.subscription.restore({\n  subscriptionId: 'sub_123'\n})\n```\n\n**Billing Portal:**\n```typescript\nawait authClient.subscription.billingPortal({\n  returnUrl: '/account'\n})\n```\n\n## Subscription Plans\n\nDefine plans statically or dynamically:\n\n```typescript\nsubscription: {\n  enabled: true,\n  plans: [\n    {\n      name: \"basic\",\n      priceId: \"price_123\",\n      annualDiscountPriceId: \"price_456\",\n      limits: { projects: 5, storage: 10 },\n      freeTrial: { days: 14 }\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n## Database Schema\n\nTables created:\n- **user** - adds `stripeCustomerId` field\n- **organization** - adds `stripeCustomerId` field\n- **subscription** - stores plan, status, billing period, trial dates, seats\n\n## Webhook Setup\n\nConfigure endpoint in Stripe dashboard:\n```\nhttps://your-domain.com/api/auth/stripe/webhook\n```\n\nRequired events:\n- `checkout.session.completed`\n- `customer.subscription.created`\n- `customer.subscription.updated`\n- `customer.subscription.deleted`\n\nHandle custom events via:\n```typescript\nonEvent: async (event) => {\n  if (event.type === \"invoice.paid\") {\n    // Handle invoice\n  }\n}\n```\n\n## Subscription Lifecycle Hooks\n\n```typescript\nsubscription: {\n  onSubscriptionComplete: async ({ subscription, plan }) => {},\n  onSubscriptionCancel: async ({ subscription }) => {},\n  onTrialEnd: async ({ subscription }) => {},\n  onTrialExpired: async (subscription) => {}\n}\n```\n\n## Key Features\n\n- Automatic Stripe customer creation on signup\n- Trial abuse prevention (one trial per account)\n- Support for team subscriptions with seats\n- Scheduled plan changes at billing period end\n- Reference system for user or organization billing"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"5ecfe1e9-6f52-4d05-b142-586fa1064d01","uuid":"76c994cc-7d65-4d13-a20c-6848328b8223","tool_use_result":{"bytes":942420,"code":200,"codeText":"OK","result":"# Better Auth Stripe Plugin Documentation Extract\n\n## Installation\n\n**Package:** `@better-auth/stripe`\n```bash\nnpm install @better-auth/stripe stripe@^20.0.0\n```\n\n## Server Configuration\n\nAdd to your `auth.ts`:\n\n```typescript\nimport { betterAuth } from \"better-auth\"\nimport { stripe } from \"@better-auth/stripe\"\nimport Stripe from \"stripe\"\n\nconst stripeClient = new Stripe(process.env.STRIPE_SECRET_KEY!)\n\nexport const auth = betterAuth({\n  plugins: [\n    stripe({\n      stripeClient,\n      stripeWebhookSecret: process.env.STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET!,\n      createCustomerOnSignUp: true\n    })\n  ]\n})\n```\n\n## Client Configuration\n\nAdd to your `auth-client.ts`:\n\n```typescript\nimport { createAuthClient } from \"better-auth/client\"\nimport { stripeClient } from \"@better-auth/stripe/client\"\n\nexport const authClient = createAuthClient({\n  plugins: [\n    stripeClient({ subscription: true })\n  ]\n})\n```\n\n## Core Methods\n\n**Upgrade/Create Subscription:**\n```typescript\nawait authClient.subscription.upgrade({\n  plan: \"pro\",\n  annual: true,\n  successUrl: \"/dashboard\",\n  cancelUrl: \"/pricing\",\n  seats: 5\n})\n```\n\n**List Active Subscriptions:**\n```typescript\nconst { data: subscriptions } = await authClient.subscription.list({\n  query: { referenceId: '123', customerType: 'user' }\n})\n```\n\n**Cancel Subscription:**\n```typescript\nawait authClient.subscription.cancel({\n  subscriptionId: 'sub_123',\n  returnUrl: '/account'\n})\n```\n\n**Restore Subscription:**\n```typescript\nawait authClient.subscription.restore({\n  subscriptionId: 'sub_123'\n})\n```\n\n**Billing Portal:**\n```typescript\nawait authClient.subscription.billingPortal({\n  returnUrl: '/account'\n})\n```\n\n## Subscription Plans\n\nDefine plans statically or dynamically:\n\n```typescript\nsubscription: {\n  enabled: true,\n  plans: [\n    {\n      name: \"basic\",\n      priceId: \"price_123\",\n      annualDiscountPriceId: \"price_456\",\n      limits: { projects: 5, storage: 10 },\n      freeTrial: { days: 14 }\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n## Database Schema\n\nTables created:\n- **user** - adds `stripeCustomerId` field\n- **organization** - adds `stripeCustomerId` field\n- **subscription** - stores plan, status, billing period, trial dates, seats\n\n## Webhook Setup\n\nConfigure endpoint in Stripe dashboard:\n```\nhttps://your-domain.com/api/auth/stripe/webhook\n```\n\nRequired events:\n- `checkout.session.completed`\n- `customer.subscription.created`\n- `customer.subscription.updated`\n- `customer.subscription.deleted`\n\nHandle custom events via:\n```typescript\nonEvent: async (event) => {\n  if (event.type === \"invoice.paid\") {\n    // Handle invoice\n  }\n}\n```\n\n## Subscription Lifecycle Hooks\n\n```typescript\nsubscription: {\n  onSubscriptionComplete: async ({ subscription, plan }) => {},\n  onSubscriptionCancel: async ({ subscription }) => {},\n  onTrialEnd: async ({ subscription }) => {},\n  onTrialExpired: async (subscription) => {}\n}\n```\n\n## Key Features\n\n- Automatic Stripe customer creation on signup\n- Trial abuse prevention (one trial per account)\n- Support for team subscriptions with seats\n- Scheduled plan changes at billing period end\n- Reference system for user or organization billing","durationMs":10236,"url":"https://www.better-auth.com/docs/plugins/stripe"}}
