{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Ee4UC9jkT2T8K6qCEPciNh","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# AGENTS.md - AI Coding Agent Reference\n     2→\n     3→This file provides essential information for AI coding agents working on this project. It contains project-specific details, conventions, and guidelines that complement the README.\n     4→\n     5→---\n     6→\n     7→## Project Overview\n     8→\n     9→**Next.js Admin Dashboard Starter** is a production-ready admin dashboard template built with:\n    10→\n    11→- **Framework**: Next.js 16 (App Router)\n    12→- **Language**: TypeScript 5.7\n    13→- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS v4\n    14→- **UI Components**: shadcn/ui (New York style)\n    15→- **Authentication**: Clerk (with Organizations/Billing support)\n    16→- **Error Tracking**: Sentry\n    17→- **Charts**: Recharts\n    18→- **Containerization**: Docker (Node.js & Bun Dockerfiles)\n    19→- **Package Manager**: Bun (preferred) or npm\n    20→\n    21→The project follows a feature-based folder structure designed for scalability in SaaS applications, internal tools, and admin panels.\n    22→\n    23→---\n    24→\n    25→## Technology Stack Details\n    26→\n    27→### Core Framework & Runtime\n    28→\n    29→- Next.js 16.0.10 with App Router\n    30→- React 19.2.0\n    31→- TypeScript 5.7.2 with strict mode enabled\n    32→\n    33→### Styling & UI\n    34→\n    35→- Tailwind CSS v4 (using `@import 'tailwindcss'` syntax)\n    36→- PostCSS with `@tailwindcss/postcss` plugin\n    37→- shadcn/ui component library (Radix UI primitives)\n    38→- CSS custom properties for theming (OKLCH color format)\n    39→\n    40→### State Management\n    41→\n    42→- Zustand 5.x for local UI state (chat, kanban, notifications)\n    43→- Nuqs for URL search params state management\n    44→- TanStack Form + Zod for form handling (via `useAppForm` hook)\n    45→\n    46→### Data Fetching & Caching\n    47→\n    48→- TanStack React Query for data fetching, caching, and mutations\n    49→- Server-side prefetching with `HydrationBoundary` + `dehydrate`\n    50→- Client-side `useQuery` + nuqs `shallow: true` for tables (no RSC round-trips on pagination/filter)\n    51→- `useMutation` + `invalidateQueries` for form submissions\n    52→- Query client singleton in `src/lib/query-client.ts`\n    53→\n    54→### Authentication & Authorization\n    55→\n    56→- Clerk for authentication and user management\n    57→- Clerk Organizations for multi-tenant workspaces\n    58→- Clerk Billing for subscription management (B2B)\n    59→- Client-side RBAC for navigation visibility\n    60→\n    61→### Data & APIs\n    62→\n    63→- TanStack Table for data tables\n    64→- TanStack React Query for data fetching and mutations\n    65→- Recharts for analytics/charts\n    66→- Service layer per feature (`api/types.ts` → `api/service.ts` → `api/queries.ts`)\n    67→- Route handlers at `src/app/api/` (for Route Handler or BFF patterns)\n    68→- Mock data in `src/constants/mock-api*.ts` (default, swap via service layer)\n    69→- API client utility in `src/lib/api-client.ts` (for fetch-based patterns)\n    70→\n    71→### Development Tools\n    72→\n    73→- ESLint 8.x with Next.js core-web-vitals config\n    74→- Prettier 3.x with prettier-plugin-tailwindcss\n    75→- Husky for git hooks\n    76→- lint-staged for pre-commit formatting\n    77→\n    78→---\n    79→\n    80→## Project Structure\n    81→\n    82→```\n    83→/src\n    84→├── app/                    # Next.js App Router\n    85→│   ├── auth/              # Authentication routes (sign-in, sign-up)\n    86→│   ├── dashboard/         # Dashboard routes\n    87→│   │   ├── overview/      # Parallel routes (@area_stats, @bar_stats, etc.)\n    88→│   │   ├── product/       # Product management pages\n    89→│   │   ├── kanban/        # Kanban board page\n    90→│   │   ├── chat/          # Messaging page\n    91→│   │   ├── notifications/ # Notifications page\n    92→│   │   ├── workspaces/    # Organization management\n    93→│   │   ├── billing/       # Subscription billing\n    94→│   │   ├── exclusive/     # Pro plan feature example\n    95→│   │   └── profile/       # User profile\n    96→│   ├── api/               # API routes (if any)\n    97→│   ├── layout.tsx         # Root layout with providers\n    98→│   ├── page.tsx           # Landing page\n    99→│   ├── global-error.tsx   # Sentry-integrated error boundary\n   100→│   └── not-found.tsx      # 404 page\n   101→│\n   102→├── components/\n   103→│   ├── ui/                # shadcn/ui components (50+ components)\n   104→│   ├── layout/            # Layout components (sidebar, header, etc.)\n   105→│   ├── forms/             # Form field wrappers\n   106→│   ├── themes/            # Theme system components\n   107→│   ├── kbar/              # Command+K search bar\n   108→│   ├── icons.tsx          # Icon registry\n   109→│   └── ...\n   110→│\n   111→├── features/              # Feature-based modules\n   112→│   ├── auth/              # Authentication components\n   113→│   ├── overview/          # Dashboard analytics\n   114→│   ├── products/          # Product management (React Query + nuqs)\n   115→│   │   ├── api/\n   116→│   │   │   ├── types.ts   # Type contract (response shapes, filters, payloads)\n   117→│   │   │   ├── service.ts # Data access layer (swap for your backend)\n   118→│   │   │   └── queries.ts # React Query options + key factories\n   119→│   │   ├── components/    # Listing, form, table components\n   120→│   │   ├── schemas/       # Zod schemas\n   121→│   │   └── constants/     # Filter options\n   122→│   ├── users/             # User management (React Query + nuqs)\n   123→│   │   ├── api/           # Same pattern: types.ts → service.ts → queries.ts\n   124→│   │   └── components/    # Listing, table components\n   125→│   ├── react-query-demo/  # React Query showcase (Pokemon API)\n   126→│   ├── kanban/            # Kanban board with dnd-kit\n   127→│   ├── chat/              # Messaging UI (conversations, bubbles, composer)\n   128→│   ├── notifications/     # Notification center & store\n   129→│   └── profile/           # Profile management\n   130→│\n   131→├── config/                # Configuration files\n   132→│   ├── nav-config.ts      # Navigation with RBAC\n   133→│   └── ...\n   134→│\n   135→├── hooks/                 # Custom React hooks\n   136→│   ├── use-nav.ts         # RBAC navigation filtering\n   137→│   ├── use-data-table.ts  # Data table state\n   138→│   └── ...\n   139→│\n   140→├── lib/                   # Utility functions\n   141→│   ├── utils.ts           # cn() and formatters\n   142→│   ├── searchparams.ts    # Search param utilities\n   143→│   └── ...\n   144→│\n   145→├── types/                 # TypeScript type definitions\n   146→│   └── index.ts           # Core types (NavItem, etc.)\n   147→│\n   148→└── styles/                # Global styles\n   149→    ├── globals.css        # Tailwind imports + view transitions\n   150→    ├── theme.css          # Theme imports\n   151→    └── themes/            # Individual theme files\n   152→\n   153→/docs                      # Documentation\n   154→│   ├── clerk_setup.md     # Clerk configuration guide\n   155→│   ├── nav-rbac.md        # Navigation RBAC documentation\n   156→│   └── themes.md          # Theme customization guide\n   157→\n   158→/scripts                   # Dev tooling\n   159→    ├── cleanup.js         # Feature removal (self-contained, delete when done)\n   160→    └── postinstall.js     # Dev server cleanup message (auto-cleans)\n   161→\n   162→Dockerfile                 # Node.js production Dockerfile\n   163→Dockerfile.bun             # Bun production Dockerfile\n   164→.dockerignore              # Docker build exclusions\n   165→```\n   166→\n   167→---\n   168→\n   169→## Build & Development Commands\n   170→\n   171→```bash\n   172→# Install dependencies\n   173→bun install\n   174→\n   175→# Development server\n   176→bun run dev          # Starts at http://localhost:3000\n   177→\n   178→# Build for production\n   179→bun run build\n   180→\n   181→# Start production server\n   182→bun run start\n   183→\n   184→# Linting\n   185→bun run lint         # Run ESLint\n   186→bun run lint:fix     # Fix ESLint issues and format\n   187→bun run lint:strict  # Zero warnings tolerance\n   188→\n   189→# Formatting\n   190→bun run format       # Format with Prettier\n   191→bun run format:check # Check formatting\n   192→\n   193→# Git hooks\n   194→bun run prepare      # Install Husky hooks\n   195→```\n   196→\n   197→---\n   198→\n   199→## Environment Configuration\n   200→\n   201→Copy `env.example.txt` to `.env.local` and configure:\n   202→\n   203→### Required for Authentication (Clerk)\n   204→\n   205→```env\n   206→NEXT_PUBLIC_CLERK_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=pk_...\n   207→CLERK_SECRET_KEY=sk_...\n   208→\n   209→# Redirect URLs\n   210→NEXT_PUBLIC_CLERK_SIGN_IN_URL=\"/auth/sign-in\"\n   211→NEXT_PUBLIC_CLERK_SIGN_UP_URL=\"/auth/sign-up\"\n   212→NEXT_PUBLIC_CLERK_AFTER_SIGN_IN_URL=\"/dashboard/overview\"\n   213→NEXT_PUBLIC_CLERK_AFTER_SIGN_UP_URL=\"/dashboard/overview\"\n   214→```\n   215→\n   216→### Optional for Error Tracking (Sentry)\n   217→\n   218→```env\n   219→NEXT_PUBLIC_SENTRY_DSN=https://...@....ingest.sentry.io/...\n   220→NEXT_PUBLIC_SENTRY_ORG=your-org\n   221→NEXT_PUBLIC_SENTRY_PROJECT=your-project\n   222→SENTRY_AUTH_TOKEN=sntrys_...\n   223→NEXT_PUBLIC_SENTRY_DISABLED=\"false\"  # Set to \"true\" to disable in dev\n   224→```\n   225→\n   226→**Note**: Clerk supports \"keyless mode\" - the app works without API keys for initial development.\n   227→\n   228→---\n   229→\n   230→## Code Style Guidelines\n   231→\n   232→### TypeScript\n   233→\n   234→- Strict mode enabled\n   235→- Use explicit return types for public functions\n   236→- Prefer interface over type for object definitions\n   237→- Use `@/*` alias for imports from src\n   238→\n   239→### Formatting (Prettier)\n   240→\n   241→```json\n   242→{\n   243→  \"singleQuote\": true,\n   244→  \"jsxSingleQuote\": true,\n   245→  \"semi\": true,\n   246→  \"trailingComma\": \"none\",\n   247→  \"tabWidth\": 2,\n   248→  \"arrowParens\": \"always\"\n   249→}\n   250→```\n   251→\n   252→### ESLint Rules\n   253→\n   254→- `@typescript-eslint/no-unused-vars`: warn\n   255→- `no-console`: warn\n   256→- `react-hooks/exhaustive-deps`: warn\n   257→- `import/no-unresolved`: off (handled by TypeScript)\n   258→\n   259→### Component Conventions\n   260→\n   261→- Use function declarations for components: `function ComponentName() {}`\n   262→- Props interface named `{ComponentName}Props`\n   263→- shadcn/ui components use `cn()` utility for class merging\n   264→- Server components by default, `'use client'` only when needed\n   265→\n   266→---\n   267→\n   268→## Theming System\n   269→\n   270→The project uses a sophisticated multi-theme system with 10 built-in themes:\n   271→\n   272→- `vercel` (default)\n   273→- `claude`\n   274→- `neobrutualism`\n   275→- `supabase`\n   276→- `mono`\n   277→- `notebook`\n   278→- `light-green`\n   279→- `zen`\n   280→- `astro-vista`\n   281→- `whatsapp`\n   282→\n   283→### Theme Files\n   284→\n   285→- CSS files: `src/styles/themes/{theme-name}.css`\n   286→- Theme registry: `src/components/themes/theme.config.ts`\n   287→- Font config: `src/components/themes/font.config.ts`\n   288→- Active theme provider: `src/components/themes/active-theme.tsx`\n   289→\n   290→### Adding a New Theme\n   291→\n   292→1. Create `src/styles/themes/your-theme.css` with `[data-theme='your-theme']` selector\n   293→2. Import in `src/styles/theme.css`\n   294→3. Add to `THEMES` array in `src/components/themes/theme.config.ts`\n   295→4. (Optional) Add fonts in `font.config.ts`\n   296→5. (Optional) Set as default in `theme.config.ts`\n   297→\n   298→See `docs/themes.md` for detailed theming guide.\n   299→\n   300→---\n   301→\n   302→## Navigation & RBAC System\n   303→\n   304→### Navigation Configuration\n   305→\n   306→Navigation is organized into groups in `src/config/nav-config.ts`:\n   307→\n   308→```typescript\n   309→import { NavGroup } from '@/types';\n   310→\n   311→export const navGroups: NavGroup[] = [\n   312→  {\n   313→    label: 'Overview',\n   314→    items: [\n   315→      {\n   316→        title: 'Dashboard',\n   317→        url: '/dashboard/overview',\n   318→        icon: 'dashboard',\n   319→        shortcut: ['d', 'd'],\n   320→        items: [],\n   321→        access: { requireOrg: true } // RBAC check\n   322→      }\n   323→    ]\n   324→  }\n   325→];\n   326→```\n   327→\n   328→### Access Control Properties\n   329→\n   330→- `requireOrg: boolean` - Requires active organization\n   331→- `permission: string` - Requires specific permission\n   332→- `role: string` - Requires specific role\n   333→- `plan: string` - Requires specific subscription plan\n   334→- `feature: string` - Requires specific feature\n   335→\n   336→### Client-Side Filtering\n   337→\n   338→The `useFilteredNavItems()` hook in `src/hooks/use-nav.ts` filters navigation client-side using Clerk's `useOrganization()` and `useUser()` hooks. This is for UX only - actual security checks must happen server-side.\n   339→\n   340→---\n   341→\n   342→## Authentication Patterns\n   343→\n   344→### Protected Routes\n   345→\n   346→Dashboard routes use Clerk's middleware pattern. Pages that require organization:\n   347→\n   348→```tsx\n   349→import { auth } from '@clerk/nextjs';\n   350→import { redirect } from 'next/navigation';\n   351→\n   352→export default async function Page() {\n   353→  const { orgId } = await auth();\n   354→  if (!orgId) redirect('/dashboard/workspaces');\n   355→  // ...\n   356→}\n   357→```\n   358→\n   359→### Plan/Feature Protection\n   360→\n   361→Use Clerk's `<Protect>` component for client-side:\n   362→\n   363→```tsx\n   364→import { Protect } from '@clerk/nextjs';\n   365→\n   366→<Protect plan='pro' fallback={<UpgradePrompt />}>\n   367→  <PremiumContent />\n   368→</Protect>;\n   369→```\n   370→\n   371→Use `has()` function for server-side checks:\n   372→\n   373→```tsx\n   374→import { auth } from '@clerk/nextjs';\n   375→\n   376→const { has } = await auth();\n   377→const hasFeature = has({ feature: 'premium_access' });\n   378→```\n   379→\n   380→---\n   381→\n   382→## Data Fetching Patterns\n   383→\n   384→### Service Layer Architecture\n   385→\n   386→Each feature has a three-file API layer:\n   387→\n   388→```\n   389→src/features/<name>/api/\n   390→  types.ts      ← Type contract (response shapes, filters, payloads)\n   391→  service.ts    ← Data access functions (the ONE file to swap for your backend)\n   392→  queries.ts    ← React Query options + query key factories (stable, never changes)\n   393→```\n   394→\n   395→**`service.ts` is the only file you modify when connecting to a real backend.** Queries and components import from it — they never change.\n   396→\n   397→#### Backend Patterns\n   398→\n   399→| Pattern                                            | How to implement                                                                            |\n   400→| -------------------------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |\n   401→| **Server Actions + ORM** (Prisma/Drizzle/Supabase) | Add `'use server'` at top of `service.ts`, call ORM directly                                |\n   402→| **Route Handlers + ORM**                           | `service.ts` calls `/api/` routes via `apiClient`, route handlers call ORM                  |\n   403→| **BFF** (Next.js proxies to Laravel/Go/etc.)       | `service.ts` calls `/api/` routes via `apiClient`, route handlers proxy to external backend |\n   404→| **Direct external API** (frontend-only)            | `service.ts` calls external URL via `fetch()`                                               |\n   405→| **Mock** (default)                                 | `service.ts` calls in-memory fake data stores                                               |\n   406→\n   407→Route handlers at `src/app/api/` are ready for patterns 2 and 3. `src/lib/api-client.ts` provides a typed `fetch` wrapper.\n   408→\n   409→### Query Key Factories\n   410→\n   411→Each feature defines a key factory in `queries.ts` for type-safe, hierarchical cache invalidation:\n   412→\n   413→```tsx\n   414→export const entityKeys = {\n   415→  all: ['entities'] as const,\n   416→  list: (filters: EntityFilters) => [...entityKeys.all, 'list', filters] as const,\n   417→  detail: (id: number) => [...entityKeys.all, 'detail', id] as const\n   418→};\n   419→\n   420→// Usage in queryOptions\n   421→queryKey: entityKeys.list(filters);\n   422→\n   423→// Usage in mutations — invalidate all entity queries\n   424→queryClient.invalidateQueries({ queryKey: entityKeys.all });\n   425→```\n   426→\n   427→### React Query (Default for all new pages)\n   428→\n   429→The project uses TanStack React Query with server-side prefetching and client-side cache management:\n   430→\n   431→1. **Query options** defined in `queries.ts` — shared between server prefetch and client hooks\n   432→2. **Server prefetch** using `void queryClient.prefetchQuery()` + `HydrationBoundary` + `dehydrate` — `void` (fire-and-forget) is the standard TanStack pattern for Next.js App Router\n   433→3. **Client fetch** using `useSuspenseQuery()` — integrates with React Suspense so prefetched data streams in without showing a loading skeleton on first load\n   434→4. **Suspense boundary** wraps the client component — shows a fallback skeleton only on subsequent client-side navigations when cache is empty\n   435→\n   436→```tsx\n   437→// Server component: prefetch + dehydrate\n   438→const queryClient = getQueryClient();\n   439→void queryClient.prefetchQuery(entitiesQueryOptions(filters)); // void, not await\n   440→\n   441→return (\n   442→  <HydrationBoundary state={dehydrate(queryClient)}>\n   443→    <Suspense fallback={<Skeleton />}>\n   444→      <EntityTable />\n   445→    </Suspense>\n   446→  </HydrationBoundary>\n   447→);\n   448→\n   449→// Client component: useSuspenseQuery (not useQuery)\n   450→const { data } = useSuspenseQuery(entitiesQueryOptions(filters));\n   451→```\n   452→\n   453→**Why `void` + `useSuspenseQuery`:**\n   454→\n   455→- `void` fires the prefetch without blocking the server component\n   456→- `useSuspenseQuery` integrates with React Suspense — the pending query streams in via Next.js streaming SSR\n   457→- With `<Suspense fallback={<Skeleton />}>`: skeleton shows immediately while data streams in — this is expected behavior, the skeleton IS the Suspense fallback during streaming\n   458→- Without `<Suspense>` wrapper: no skeleton, but the previous page stays visible until data fully resolves (feels like a slow navigation)\n   459→- Once data is cached (within `staleTime`), subsequent visits are instant — no skeleton\n   460→\n   461→**Why NOT `useQuery`:**\n   462→\n   463→- `useQuery` doesn't integrate with Suspense — returns `isLoading: true` and you must handle loading state manually\n   464→- Hydrated pending queries from `void` prefetch won't prevent the loading state\n   465→- Results in skeleton flash even when data is prefetched\n   466→\n   467→### Mutations\n   468→\n   469→Components import service functions for mutations. Use query key factories for invalidation:\n   470→\n   471→```tsx\n   472→import { createEntity } from '../api/service';\n   473→import { entityKeys } from '../api/queries';\n   474→\n   475→const mutation = useMutation({\n   476→  mutationFn: (data) => createEntity(data),\n   477→  onSuccess: () => {\n   478→    queryClient.invalidateQueries({ queryKey: entityKeys.all });\n   479→    toast.success('Created');\n   480→  }\n   481→});\n   482→```\n   483→\n   484→### URL State Management\n   485→\n   486→Use `nuqs` for search params state:\n   487→\n   488→- `searchParamsCache` (server) — reads params in server components\n   489→- `useQueryState` (client) — reads/writes params in client components with `shallow: true`\n   490→\n   491→### Data Tables\n   492→\n   493→Tables use TanStack Table with React Query:\n   494→\n   495→- Query options in `features/*/api/queries.ts`\n   496→- Column definitions in `features/*/components/*-tables/columns.tsx`\n   497→- Table component in `src/components/ui/table/data-table.tsx`\n   498→- Column pinning via `initialState.columnPinning` in `useDataTable`\n   499→\n   500→---\n   501→\n   502→## Error Handling & Monitoring\n   503→\n   504→### Sentry Integration\n   505→\n   506→Sentry is configured for both client and server:\n   507→\n   508→- Client config: `src/instrumentation-client.ts`\n   509→- Server config: `src/instrumentation.ts`\n   510→- Global error: `src/app/global-error.tsx`\n   511→\n   512→To disable Sentry in development:\n   513→\n   514→```env\n   515→NEXT_PUBLIC_SENTRY_DISABLED=\"true\"\n   516→```\n   517→\n   518→### Error Boundaries\n   519→\n   520→- `global-error.tsx` - Catches all errors, reports to Sentry\n   521→- Parallel route `error.tsx` files for specific sections\n   522→\n   523→---\n   524→\n   525→## Testing Strategy\n   526→\n   527→**Note**: This project does not include a test suite by default. Consider adding:\n   528→\n   529→- **Unit tests**: Vitest or Jest for utilities and hooks\n   530→- **Component tests**: React Testing Library for UI components\n   531→- **E2E tests**: Playwright for critical user flows\n   532→\n   533→Recommended test locations:\n   534→\n   535→```\n   536→/src\n   537→  /__tests__           # Unit tests\n   538→  /features/*/tests    # Feature tests\n   539→/e2e                   # Playwright tests\n   540→```\n   541→\n   542→---\n   543→\n   544→## Deployment\n   545→\n   546→### Vercel (Recommended)\n   547→\n   548→1. Connect repository to Vercel\n   549→2. Add environment variables in dashboard\n   550→3. Deploy\n   551→\n   552→### Environment Variables for Production\n   553→\n   554→Ensure these are set in your deployment platform:\n   555→\n   556→- `NEXT_PUBLIC_CLERK_PUBLISHABLE_KEY`\n   557→- `CLERK_SECRET_KEY`\n   558→- All `NEXT_PUBLIC_*` variables for client-side access\n   559→- `SENTRY_*` variables if using error tracking\n   560→\n   561→### Docker\n   562→\n   563→Production-ready Dockerfiles are included:\n   564→\n   565→- `Dockerfile` — Node.js-based\n   566→- `Dockerfile.bun` — Bun-based\n   567→\n   568→Both use `output: 'standalone'` in `next.config.ts`. Pass `NEXT_PUBLIC_*` vars as `--build-arg` at build time, and runtime secrets via `-e` at run time.\n   569→\n   570→### Build Considerations\n   571→\n   572→- Output: `standalone` (optimized for Docker/self-hosting)\n   573→- Images: Configured for `api.slingacademy.com`, `img.clerk.com`, `clerk.com`\n   574→- Sentry source maps uploaded automatically in CI\n   575→\n   576→---\n   577→\n   578→## Feature Cleanup System\n   579→\n   580→A single `scripts/cleanup.js` file handles removal of optional features:\n   581→\n   582→```bash\n   583→# Interactive mode — prompts for each feature\n   584→node scripts/cleanup.js --interactive\n   585→\n   586→# Remove specific features\n   587→node scripts/cleanup.js clerk           # Remove auth/org/billing\n   588→node scripts/cleanup.js kanban          # Remove kanban board\n   589→node scripts/cleanup.js chat            # Remove messaging UI\n   590→node scripts/cleanup.js notifications   # Remove notification center\n   591→node scripts/cleanup.js themes          # Keep one theme, remove rest\n   592→node scripts/cleanup.js sentry          # Remove error tracking\n   593→\n   594→# Remove multiple at once\n   595→node scripts/cleanup.js kanban chat notifications\n   596→\n   597→# Preview without changing files\n   598→node scripts/cleanup.js --dry-run kanban\n   599→\n   600→# List all features\n   601→node scripts/cleanup.js --list\n   602→```\n   603→\n   604→**Safety**: Script requires git repository with at least one commit. Use `--force` to skip.\n   605→\n   606→After cleanup, delete `scripts/cleanup.js` — the dev server message auto-cleans on next start.\n   607→\n   608→---\n   609→\n   610→## Icon System\n   611→\n   612→**All icons come from a single source: `src/components/icons.tsx`.**\n   613→\n   614→The project uses `@tabler/icons-react` as the sole icon package. Every icon is re-exported through a centralized `Icons` object — **never import directly from `@tabler/icons-react` or any other icon package**.\n   615→\n   616→### Usage\n   617→\n   618→```tsx\n   619→import { Icons } from '@/components/icons';\n   620→\n   621→// In JSX\n   622→<Icons.search className='h-4 w-4' />\n   623→<Icons.chevronRight className='h-4 w-4' />\n   624→\n   625→// Passing as a prop\n   626→icon={Icons.check}\n   627→```\n   628→\n   629→### Adding a New Icon\n   630→\n   631→1. Import the tabler icon in `src/components/icons.tsx`\n   632→2. Add a semantic key to the `Icons` object\n   633→3. Use `Icons.yourKey` everywhere — never the raw import\n   634→\n   635→```tsx\n   636→// In src/components/icons.tsx\n   637→import { IconNewIcon } from '@tabler/icons-react';\n   638→\n   639→export const Icons = {\n   640→  // ...existing icons\n   641→  newIcon: IconNewIcon\n   642→};\n   643→```\n   644→\n   645→### Available Icon Categories\n   646→\n   647→| Category        | Example Keys                                                                  |\n   648→| --------------- | ----------------------------------------------------------------------------- |\n   649→| General         | `check`, `close`, `search`, `settings`, `trash`, `spinner`, `info`, `warning` |\n   650→| Navigation      | `chevronDown`, `chevronLeft`, `chevronRight`, `chevronUp`, `chevronsUpDown`   |\n   651→| Layout          | `dashboard`, `kanban`, `panelLeft`                                            |\n   652→| User            | `user`, `account`, `profile`, `teams`                                         |\n   653→| Communication   | `chat`, `notification`, `phone`, `video`, `send`                              |\n   654→| Files           | `page`, `post`, `media`, `fileTypePdf`, `fileTypeDoc`                         |\n   655→| Actions         | `add`, `edit`, `upload`, `share`, `login`, `logout`                           |\n   656→| Theme           | `sun`, `moon`, `brightness`, `laptop`, `palette`                              |\n   657→| Text formatting | `bold`, `italic`, `underline`, `text`                                         |\n   658→| Data / Charts   | `trendingUp`, `trendingDown`, `eyeOff`, `adjustments`                         |\n   659→\n   660→### Icon Showcase Page\n   661→\n   662→Browse all available icons at `/dashboard/elements/icons` — a searchable grid of every icon in the registry.\n   663→\n   664→### Why This Pattern?\n   665→\n   666→- **Single source of truth** — swap icon packages by editing one file\n   667→- **Semantic naming** — `Icons.trash` is clearer than `IconTrash` scattered across files\n   668→- **Discoverability** — autocomplete on `Icons.` shows every available icon\n   669→- **No direct dependencies** — components never couple to a specific icon package\n   670→\n   671→---\n   672→\n   673→## Common Development Tasks\n   674→\n   675→### Adding a New Feature (End-to-End)\n   676→\n   677→1. Create `src/features/<name>/api/types.ts` — response types, filter types, mutation payloads\n   678→2. Create `src/features/<name>/api/service.ts` — data access functions (mock by default)\n   679→3. Create `src/features/<name>/api/queries.ts` — query key factory + `queryOptions`\n   680→4. Create page route: `src/app/dashboard/<name>/page.tsx`\n   681→5. Create feature components in `src/features/<name>/components/`\n   682→6. Add navigation item in `src/config/nav-config.ts`\n   683→7. (Optional) Add route handlers in `src/app/api/<name>/` for REST API patterns\n   684→8. (Optional) Register new icon in `src/components/icons.tsx`\n   685→\n   686→### Adding a New API Route\n   687→\n   688→1. Create: `src/app/api/my-route/route.ts`\n   689→2. Export HTTP method handlers: `GET`, `POST`, etc.\n   690→3. For BFF pattern: proxy requests to your external backend\n   691→\n   692→### Adding a shadcn Component\n   693→\n   694→```bash\n   695→npx shadcn add component-name\n   696→```\n   697→\n   698→### Adding a New Theme\n   699→\n   700→See \"Theming System\" section above or `docs/themes.md`.\n   701→\n   702→---\n   703→\n   704→## Troubleshooting\n   705→\n   706→### Common Issues\n   707→\n   708→**Build fails with Tailwind errors**\n   709→\n   710→- Ensure using Tailwind CSS v4 syntax (`@import 'tailwindcss'`)\n   711→- Check `postcss.config.js` uses `@tailwindcss/postcss`\n   712→\n   713→**Clerk keyless mode popup**\n   714→\n   715→- Normal in development without API keys\n   716→- Click popup to claim application or set env variables\n   717→\n   718→**Theme not applying**\n   719→\n   720→- Check theme name matches in CSS `[data-theme]` and `theme.config.ts`\n   721→- Verify theme CSS is imported in `theme.css`\n   722→\n   723→**Navigation items not showing**\n   724→\n   725→- Check `access` property in nav config\n   726→- Verify user has required org/permission/role\n   727→\n   728→---\n   729→\n   730→## External Documentation\n   731→\n   732→- [Next.js App Router](https://nextjs.org/docs/app)\n   733→- [Clerk Next.js SDK](https://clerk.com/docs/references/nextjs)\n   734→- [shadcn/ui](https://ui.shadcn.com/docs)\n   735→- [Tailwind CSS v4](https://tailwindcss.com/docs)\n   736→- [TanStack Table](https://tanstack.com/table/latest)\n   737→- [Sentry Next.js](https://docs.sentry.io/platforms/javascript/guides/nextjs/)\n   738→\n   739→---\n   740→\n   741→## Notes for AI Agents\n   742→\n   743→1. **Always use `cn()` for className merging** - never concatenate strings manually\n   744→2. **Respect the feature-based structure** - put new feature code in `src/features/`\n   745→3. **Server components by default** - only add `'use client'` when using browser APIs or React hooks\n   746→4. **Type safety first** - avoid `any`, prefer explicit types\n   747→5. **Follow existing patterns** - look at similar components before creating new ones\n   748→6. **Environment variables** - prefix with `NEXT_PUBLIC_` for client-side access\n   749→7. **shadcn components** - don't modify files in `src/components/ui/` directly; extend them instead\n   750→8. **Icons** - NEVER import icons directly from `@tabler/icons-react` or any other icon package. All icons must be registered in `src/components/icons.tsx` and imported as `import { Icons } from '@/components/icons'`. To add a new icon: add the tabler import to `icons.tsx`, add a semantic key to the `Icons` object, then use `Icons.keyName` in your component.\n   751→9. **Page headers** - Always use `PageContainer` props (`pageTitle`, `pageDescription`, `pageHeaderAction`) for page headers. Never import `<Heading>` manually in pages — `PageContainer` handles that internally.\n   752→10. **Forms** - Use TanStack Form via `useAppForm` from `@/components/ui/tanstack-form`. Never use `useState` inside `AppField` render props — extract stateful logic into separate components.\n   753→11. **Button loading** - Use `<Button isLoading={isPending}>` for loading states. Uses CSS Grid overlap trick for zero layout shift. When `isLoading` is not passed, button behaves as default shadcn. `SubmitButton` in forms handles this automatically via form `isSubmitting` state.\n   754→12. **Data layer** - Always go through the service layer: `types.ts` → `service.ts` → `queries.ts`. Components import types from `types.ts`, functions from `service.ts`, query options from `queries.ts`. Never import from `@/constants/mock-api*` directly in components.\n   755→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ce8911dc-a828-4e89-bfb5-264eebf8fb2a","uuid":"d743b619-3757-46c7-98b1-0a2f2013c505","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/bogdantarasenko/Desktop/hackinterview-tool/next-shadcn-dashboard-starter/AGENTS.md","content":"# AGENTS.md - AI Coding Agent Reference\n\nThis file provides essential information for AI coding agents working on this project. It contains project-specific details, conventions, and guidelines that complement the README.\n\n---\n\n## Project Overview\n\n**Next.js Admin Dashboard Starter** is a production-ready admin dashboard template built with:\n\n- **Framework**: Next.js 16 (App Router)\n- **Language**: TypeScript 5.7\n- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS v4\n- **UI Components**: shadcn/ui (New York style)\n- **Authentication**: Clerk (with Organizations/Billing support)\n- **Error Tracking**: Sentry\n- **Charts**: Recharts\n- **Containerization**: Docker (Node.js & Bun Dockerfiles)\n- **Package Manager**: Bun (preferred) or npm\n\nThe project follows a feature-based folder structure designed for scalability in SaaS applications, internal tools, and admin panels.\n\n---\n\n## Technology Stack Details\n\n### Core Framework & Runtime\n\n- Next.js 16.0.10 with App Router\n- React 19.2.0\n- TypeScript 5.7.2 with strict mode enabled\n\n### Styling & UI\n\n- Tailwind CSS v4 (using `@import 'tailwindcss'` syntax)\n- PostCSS with `@tailwindcss/postcss` plugin\n- shadcn/ui component library (Radix UI primitives)\n- CSS custom properties for theming (OKLCH color format)\n\n### State Management\n\n- Zustand 5.x for local UI state (chat, kanban, notifications)\n- Nuqs for URL search params state management\n- TanStack Form + Zod for form handling (via `useAppForm` hook)\n\n### Data Fetching & Caching\n\n- TanStack React Query for data fetching, caching, and mutations\n- Server-side prefetching with `HydrationBoundary` + `dehydrate`\n- Client-side `useQuery` + nuqs `shallow: true` for tables (no RSC round-trips on pagination/filter)\n- `useMutation` + `invalidateQueries` for form submissions\n- Query client singleton in `src/lib/query-client.ts`\n\n### Authentication & Authorization\n\n- Clerk for authentication and user management\n- Clerk Organizations for multi-tenant workspaces\n- Clerk Billing for subscription management (B2B)\n- Client-side RBAC for navigation visibility\n\n### Data & APIs\n\n- TanStack Table for data tables\n- TanStack React Query for data fetching and mutations\n- Recharts for analytics/charts\n- Service layer per feature (`api/types.ts` → `api/service.ts` → `api/queries.ts`)\n- Route handlers at `src/app/api/` (for Route Handler or BFF patterns)\n- Mock data in `src/constants/mock-api*.ts` (default, swap via service layer)\n- API client utility in `src/lib/api-client.ts` (for fetch-based patterns)\n\n### Development Tools\n\n- ESLint 8.x with Next.js core-web-vitals config\n- Prettier 3.x with prettier-plugin-tailwindcss\n- Husky for git hooks\n- lint-staged for pre-commit formatting\n\n---\n\n## Project Structure\n\n```\n/src\n├── app/                    # Next.js App Router\n│   ├── auth/              # Authentication routes (sign-in, sign-up)\n│   ├── dashboard/         # Dashboard routes\n│   │   ├── overview/      # Parallel routes (@area_stats, @bar_stats, etc.)\n│   │   ├── product/       # Product management pages\n│   │   ├── kanban/        # Kanban board page\n│   │   ├── chat/          # Messaging page\n│   │   ├── notifications/ # Notifications page\n│   │   ├── workspaces/    # Organization management\n│   │   ├── billing/       # Subscription billing\n│   │   ├── exclusive/     # Pro plan feature example\n│   │   └── profile/       # User profile\n│   ├── api/               # API routes (if any)\n│   ├── layout.tsx         # Root layout with providers\n│   ├── page.tsx           # Landing page\n│   ├── global-error.tsx   # Sentry-integrated error boundary\n│   └── not-found.tsx      # 404 page\n│\n├── components/\n│   ├── ui/                # shadcn/ui components (50+ components)\n│   ├── layout/            # Layout components (sidebar, header, etc.)\n│   ├── forms/             # Form field wrappers\n│   ├── themes/            # Theme system components\n│   ├── kbar/              # Command+K search bar\n│   ├── icons.tsx          # Icon registry\n│   └── ...\n│\n├── features/              # Feature-based modules\n│   ├── auth/              # Authentication components\n│   ├── overview/          # Dashboard analytics\n│   ├── products/          # Product management (React Query + nuqs)\n│   │   ├── api/\n│   │   │   ├── types.ts   # Type contract (response shapes, filters, payloads)\n│   │   │   ├── service.ts # Data access layer (swap for your backend)\n│   │   │   └── queries.ts # React Query options + key factories\n│   │   ├── components/    # Listing, form, table components\n│   │   ├── schemas/       # Zod schemas\n│   │   └── constants/     # Filter options\n│   ├── users/             # User management (React Query + nuqs)\n│   │   ├── api/           # Same pattern: types.ts → service.ts → queries.ts\n│   │   └── components/    # Listing, table components\n│   ├── react-query-demo/  # React Query showcase (Pokemon API)\n│   ├── kanban/            # Kanban board with dnd-kit\n│   ├── chat/              # Messaging UI (conversations, bubbles, composer)\n│   ├── notifications/     # Notification center & store\n│   └── profile/           # Profile management\n│\n├── config/                # Configuration files\n│   ├── nav-config.ts      # Navigation with RBAC\n│   └── ...\n│\n├── hooks/                 # Custom React hooks\n│   ├── use-nav.ts         # RBAC navigation filtering\n│   ├── use-data-table.ts  # Data table state\n│   └── ...\n│\n├── lib/                   # Utility functions\n│   ├── utils.ts           # cn() and formatters\n│   ├── searchparams.ts    # Search param utilities\n│   └── ...\n│\n├── types/                 # TypeScript type definitions\n│   └── index.ts           # Core types (NavItem, etc.)\n│\n└── styles/                # Global styles\n    ├── globals.css        # Tailwind imports + view transitions\n    ├── theme.css          # Theme imports\n    └── themes/            # Individual theme files\n\n/docs                      # Documentation\n│   ├── clerk_setup.md     # Clerk configuration guide\n│   ├── nav-rbac.md        # Navigation RBAC documentation\n│   └── themes.md          # Theme customization guide\n\n/scripts                   # Dev tooling\n    ├── cleanup.js         # Feature removal (self-contained, delete when done)\n    └── postinstall.js     # Dev server cleanup message (auto-cleans)\n\nDockerfile                 # Node.js production Dockerfile\nDockerfile.bun             # Bun production Dockerfile\n.dockerignore              # Docker build exclusions\n```\n\n---\n\n## Build & Development Commands\n\n```bash\n# Install dependencies\nbun install\n\n# Development server\nbun run dev          # Starts at http://localhost:3000\n\n# Build for production\nbun run build\n\n# Start production server\nbun run start\n\n# Linting\nbun run lint         # Run ESLint\nbun run lint:fix     # Fix ESLint issues and format\nbun run lint:strict  # Zero warnings tolerance\n\n# Formatting\nbun run format       # Format with Prettier\nbun run format:check # Check formatting\n\n# Git hooks\nbun run prepare      # Install Husky hooks\n```\n\n---\n\n## Environment Configuration\n\nCopy `env.example.txt` to `.env.local` and configure:\n\n### Required for Authentication (Clerk)\n\n```env\nNEXT_PUBLIC_CLERK_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=pk_...\nCLERK_SECRET_KEY=sk_...\n\n# Redirect URLs\nNEXT_PUBLIC_CLERK_SIGN_IN_URL=\"/auth/sign-in\"\nNEXT_PUBLIC_CLERK_SIGN_UP_URL=\"/auth/sign-up\"\nNEXT_PUBLIC_CLERK_AFTER_SIGN_IN_URL=\"/dashboard/overview\"\nNEXT_PUBLIC_CLERK_AFTER_SIGN_UP_URL=\"/dashboard/overview\"\n```\n\n### Optional for Error Tracking (Sentry)\n\n```env\nNEXT_PUBLIC_SENTRY_DSN=https://...@....ingest.sentry.io/...\nNEXT_PUBLIC_SENTRY_ORG=your-org\nNEXT_PUBLIC_SENTRY_PROJECT=your-project\nSENTRY_AUTH_TOKEN=sntrys_...\nNEXT_PUBLIC_SENTRY_DISABLED=\"false\"  # Set to \"true\" to disable in dev\n```\n\n**Note**: Clerk supports \"keyless mode\" - the app works without API keys for initial development.\n\n---\n\n## Code Style Guidelines\n\n### TypeScript\n\n- Strict mode enabled\n- Use explicit return types for public functions\n- Prefer interface over type for object definitions\n- Use `@/*` alias for imports from src\n\n### Formatting (Prettier)\n\n```json\n{\n  \"singleQuote\": true,\n  \"jsxSingleQuote\": true,\n  \"semi\": true,\n  \"trailingComma\": \"none\",\n  \"tabWidth\": 2,\n  \"arrowParens\": \"always\"\n}\n```\n\n### ESLint Rules\n\n- `@typescript-eslint/no-unused-vars`: warn\n- `no-console`: warn\n- `react-hooks/exhaustive-deps`: warn\n- `import/no-unresolved`: off (handled by TypeScript)\n\n### Component Conventions\n\n- Use function declarations for components: `function ComponentName() {}`\n- Props interface named `{ComponentName}Props`\n- shadcn/ui components use `cn()` utility for class merging\n- Server components by default, `'use client'` only when needed\n\n---\n\n## Theming System\n\nThe project uses a sophisticated multi-theme system with 10 built-in themes:\n\n- `vercel` (default)\n- `claude`\n- `neobrutualism`\n- `supabase`\n- `mono`\n- `notebook`\n- `light-green`\n- `zen`\n- `astro-vista`\n- `whatsapp`\n\n### Theme Files\n\n- CSS files: `src/styles/themes/{theme-name}.css`\n- Theme registry: `src/components/themes/theme.config.ts`\n- Font config: `src/components/themes/font.config.ts`\n- Active theme provider: `src/components/themes/active-theme.tsx`\n\n### Adding a New Theme\n\n1. Create `src/styles/themes/your-theme.css` with `[data-theme='your-theme']` selector\n2. Import in `src/styles/theme.css`\n3. Add to `THEMES` array in `src/components/themes/theme.config.ts`\n4. (Optional) Add fonts in `font.config.ts`\n5. (Optional) Set as default in `theme.config.ts`\n\nSee `docs/themes.md` for detailed theming guide.\n\n---\n\n## Navigation & RBAC System\n\n### Navigation Configuration\n\nNavigation is organized into groups in `src/config/nav-config.ts`:\n\n```typescript\nimport { NavGroup } from '@/types';\n\nexport const navGroups: NavGroup[] = [\n  {\n    label: 'Overview',\n    items: [\n      {\n        title: 'Dashboard',\n        url: '/dashboard/overview',\n        icon: 'dashboard',\n        shortcut: ['d', 'd'],\n        items: [],\n        access: { requireOrg: true } // RBAC check\n      }\n    ]\n  }\n];\n```\n\n### Access Control Properties\n\n- `requireOrg: boolean` - Requires active organization\n- `permission: string` - Requires specific permission\n- `role: string` - Requires specific role\n- `plan: string` - Requires specific subscription plan\n- `feature: string` - Requires specific feature\n\n### Client-Side Filtering\n\nThe `useFilteredNavItems()` hook in `src/hooks/use-nav.ts` filters navigation client-side using Clerk's `useOrganization()` and `useUser()` hooks. This is for UX only - actual security checks must happen server-side.\n\n---\n\n## Authentication Patterns\n\n### Protected Routes\n\nDashboard routes use Clerk's middleware pattern. Pages that require organization:\n\n```tsx\nimport { auth } from '@clerk/nextjs';\nimport { redirect } from 'next/navigation';\n\nexport default async function Page() {\n  const { orgId } = await auth();\n  if (!orgId) redirect('/dashboard/workspaces');\n  // ...\n}\n```\n\n### Plan/Feature Protection\n\nUse Clerk's `<Protect>` component for client-side:\n\n```tsx\nimport { Protect } from '@clerk/nextjs';\n\n<Protect plan='pro' fallback={<UpgradePrompt />}>\n  <PremiumContent />\n</Protect>;\n```\n\nUse `has()` function for server-side checks:\n\n```tsx\nimport { auth } from '@clerk/nextjs';\n\nconst { has } = await auth();\nconst hasFeature = has({ feature: 'premium_access' });\n```\n\n---\n\n## Data Fetching Patterns\n\n### Service Layer Architecture\n\nEach feature has a three-file API layer:\n\n```\nsrc/features/<name>/api/\n  types.ts      ← Type contract (response shapes, filters, payloads)\n  service.ts    ← Data access functions (the ONE file to swap for your backend)\n  queries.ts    ← React Query options + query key factories (stable, never changes)\n```\n\n**`service.ts` is the only file you modify when connecting to a real backend.** Queries and components import from it — they never change.\n\n#### Backend Patterns\n\n| Pattern                                            | How to implement                                                                            |\n| -------------------------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |\n| **Server Actions + ORM** (Prisma/Drizzle/Supabase) | Add `'use server'` at top of `service.ts`, call ORM directly                                |\n| **Route Handlers + ORM**                           | `service.ts` calls `/api/` routes via `apiClient`, route handlers call ORM                  |\n| **BFF** (Next.js proxies to Laravel/Go/etc.)       | `service.ts` calls `/api/` routes via `apiClient`, route handlers proxy to external backend |\n| **Direct external API** (frontend-only)            | `service.ts` calls external URL via `fetch()`                                               |\n| **Mock** (default)                                 | `service.ts` calls in-memory fake data stores                                               |\n\nRoute handlers at `src/app/api/` are ready for patterns 2 and 3. `src/lib/api-client.ts` provides a typed `fetch` wrapper.\n\n### Query Key Factories\n\nEach feature defines a key factory in `queries.ts` for type-safe, hierarchical cache invalidation:\n\n```tsx\nexport const entityKeys = {\n  all: ['entities'] as const,\n  list: (filters: EntityFilters) => [...entityKeys.all, 'list', filters] as const,\n  detail: (id: number) => [...entityKeys.all, 'detail', id] as const\n};\n\n// Usage in queryOptions\nqueryKey: entityKeys.list(filters);\n\n// Usage in mutations — invalidate all entity queries\nqueryClient.invalidateQueries({ queryKey: entityKeys.all });\n```\n\n### React Query (Default for all new pages)\n\nThe project uses TanStack React Query with server-side prefetching and client-side cache management:\n\n1. **Query options** defined in `queries.ts` — shared between server prefetch and client hooks\n2. **Server prefetch** using `void queryClient.prefetchQuery()` + `HydrationBoundary` + `dehydrate` — `void` (fire-and-forget) is the standard TanStack pattern for Next.js App Router\n3. **Client fetch** using `useSuspenseQuery()` — integrates with React Suspense so prefetched data streams in without showing a loading skeleton on first load\n4. **Suspense boundary** wraps the client component — shows a fallback skeleton only on subsequent client-side navigations when cache is empty\n\n```tsx\n// Server component: prefetch + dehydrate\nconst queryClient = getQueryClient();\nvoid queryClient.prefetchQuery(entitiesQueryOptions(filters)); // void, not await\n\nreturn (\n  <HydrationBoundary state={dehydrate(queryClient)}>\n    <Suspense fallback={<Skeleton />}>\n      <EntityTable />\n    </Suspense>\n  </HydrationBoundary>\n);\n\n// Client component: useSuspenseQuery (not useQuery)\nconst { data } = useSuspenseQuery(entitiesQueryOptions(filters));\n```\n\n**Why `void` + `useSuspenseQuery`:**\n\n- `void` fires the prefetch without blocking the server component\n- `useSuspenseQuery` integrates with React Suspense — the pending query streams in via Next.js streaming SSR\n- With `<Suspense fallback={<Skeleton />}>`: skeleton shows immediately while data streams in — this is expected behavior, the skeleton IS the Suspense fallback during streaming\n- Without `<Suspense>` wrapper: no skeleton, but the previous page stays visible until data fully resolves (feels like a slow navigation)\n- Once data is cached (within `staleTime`), subsequent visits are instant — no skeleton\n\n**Why NOT `useQuery`:**\n\n- `useQuery` doesn't integrate with Suspense — returns `isLoading: true` and you must handle loading state manually\n- Hydrated pending queries from `void` prefetch won't prevent the loading state\n- Results in skeleton flash even when data is prefetched\n\n### Mutations\n\nComponents import service functions for mutations. Use query key factories for invalidation:\n\n```tsx\nimport { createEntity } from '../api/service';\nimport { entityKeys } from '../api/queries';\n\nconst mutation = useMutation({\n  mutationFn: (data) => createEntity(data),\n  onSuccess: () => {\n    queryClient.invalidateQueries({ queryKey: entityKeys.all });\n    toast.success('Created');\n  }\n});\n```\n\n### URL State Management\n\nUse `nuqs` for search params state:\n\n- `searchParamsCache` (server) — reads params in server components\n- `useQueryState` (client) — reads/writes params in client components with `shallow: true`\n\n### Data Tables\n\nTables use TanStack Table with React Query:\n\n- Query options in `features/*/api/queries.ts`\n- Column definitions in `features/*/components/*-tables/columns.tsx`\n- Table component in `src/components/ui/table/data-table.tsx`\n- Column pinning via `initialState.columnPinning` in `useDataTable`\n\n---\n\n## Error Handling & Monitoring\n\n### Sentry Integration\n\nSentry is configured for both client and server:\n\n- Client config: `src/instrumentation-client.ts`\n- Server config: `src/instrumentation.ts`\n- Global error: `src/app/global-error.tsx`\n\nTo disable Sentry in development:\n\n```env\nNEXT_PUBLIC_SENTRY_DISABLED=\"true\"\n```\n\n### Error Boundaries\n\n- `global-error.tsx` - Catches all errors, reports to Sentry\n- Parallel route `error.tsx` files for specific sections\n\n---\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n**Note**: This project does not include a test suite by default. Consider adding:\n\n- **Unit tests**: Vitest or Jest for utilities and hooks\n- **Component tests**: React Testing Library for UI components\n- **E2E tests**: Playwright for critical user flows\n\nRecommended test locations:\n\n```\n/src\n  /__tests__           # Unit tests\n  /features/*/tests    # Feature tests\n/e2e                   # Playwright tests\n```\n\n---\n\n## Deployment\n\n### Vercel (Recommended)\n\n1. Connect repository to Vercel\n2. Add environment variables in dashboard\n3. Deploy\n\n### Environment Variables for Production\n\nEnsure these are set in your deployment platform:\n\n- `NEXT_PUBLIC_CLERK_PUBLISHABLE_KEY`\n- `CLERK_SECRET_KEY`\n- All `NEXT_PUBLIC_*` variables for client-side access\n- `SENTRY_*` variables if using error tracking\n\n### Docker\n\nProduction-ready Dockerfiles are included:\n\n- `Dockerfile` — Node.js-based\n- `Dockerfile.bun` — Bun-based\n\nBoth use `output: 'standalone'` in `next.config.ts`. Pass `NEXT_PUBLIC_*` vars as `--build-arg` at build time, and runtime secrets via `-e` at run time.\n\n### Build Considerations\n\n- Output: `standalone` (optimized for Docker/self-hosting)\n- Images: Configured for `api.slingacademy.com`, `img.clerk.com`, `clerk.com`\n- Sentry source maps uploaded automatically in CI\n\n---\n\n## Feature Cleanup System\n\nA single `scripts/cleanup.js` file handles removal of optional features:\n\n```bash\n# Interactive mode — prompts for each feature\nnode scripts/cleanup.js --interactive\n\n# Remove specific features\nnode scripts/cleanup.js clerk           # Remove auth/org/billing\nnode scripts/cleanup.js kanban          # Remove kanban board\nnode scripts/cleanup.js chat            # Remove messaging UI\nnode scripts/cleanup.js notifications   # Remove notification center\nnode scripts/cleanup.js themes          # Keep one theme, remove rest\nnode scripts/cleanup.js sentry          # Remove error tracking\n\n# Remove multiple at once\nnode scripts/cleanup.js kanban chat notifications\n\n# Preview without changing files\nnode scripts/cleanup.js --dry-run kanban\n\n# List all features\nnode scripts/cleanup.js --list\n```\n\n**Safety**: Script requires git repository with at least one commit. Use `--force` to skip.\n\nAfter cleanup, delete `scripts/cleanup.js` — the dev server message auto-cleans on next start.\n\n---\n\n## Icon System\n\n**All icons come from a single source: `src/components/icons.tsx`.**\n\nThe project uses `@tabler/icons-react` as the sole icon package. Every icon is re-exported through a centralized `Icons` object — **never import directly from `@tabler/icons-react` or any other icon package**.\n\n### Usage\n\n```tsx\nimport { Icons } from '@/components/icons';\n\n// In JSX\n<Icons.search className='h-4 w-4' />\n<Icons.chevronRight className='h-4 w-4' />\n\n// Passing as a prop\nicon={Icons.check}\n```\n\n### Adding a New Icon\n\n1. Import the tabler icon in `src/components/icons.tsx`\n2. Add a semantic key to the `Icons` object\n3. Use `Icons.yourKey` everywhere — never the raw import\n\n```tsx\n// In src/components/icons.tsx\nimport { IconNewIcon } from '@tabler/icons-react';\n\nexport const Icons = {\n  // ...existing icons\n  newIcon: IconNewIcon\n};\n```\n\n### Available Icon Categories\n\n| Category        | Example Keys                                                                  |\n| --------------- | ----------------------------------------------------------------------------- |\n| General         | `check`, `close`, `search`, `settings`, `trash`, `spinner`, `info`, `warning` |\n| Navigation      | `chevronDown`, `chevronLeft`, `chevronRight`, `chevronUp`, `chevronsUpDown`   |\n| Layout          | `dashboard`, `kanban`, `panelLeft`                                            |\n| User            | `user`, `account`, `profile`, `teams`                                         |\n| Communication   | `chat`, `notification`, `phone`, `video`, `send`                              |\n| Files           | `page`, `post`, `media`, `fileTypePdf`, `fileTypeDoc`                         |\n| Actions         | `add`, `edit`, `upload`, `share`, `login`, `logout`                           |\n| Theme           | `sun`, `moon`, `brightness`, `laptop`, `palette`                              |\n| Text formatting | `bold`, `italic`, `underline`, `text`                                         |\n| Data / Charts   | `trendingUp`, `trendingDown`, `eyeOff`, `adjustments`                         |\n\n### Icon Showcase Page\n\nBrowse all available icons at `/dashboard/elements/icons` — a searchable grid of every icon in the registry.\n\n### Why This Pattern?\n\n- **Single source of truth** — swap icon packages by editing one file\n- **Semantic naming** — `Icons.trash` is clearer than `IconTrash` scattered across files\n- **Discoverability** — autocomplete on `Icons.` shows every available icon\n- **No direct dependencies** — components never couple to a specific icon package\n\n---\n\n## Common Development Tasks\n\n### Adding a New Feature (End-to-End)\n\n1. Create `src/features/<name>/api/types.ts` — response types, filter types, mutation payloads\n2. Create `src/features/<name>/api/service.ts` — data access functions (mock by default)\n3. Create `src/features/<name>/api/queries.ts` — query key factory + `queryOptions`\n4. Create page route: `src/app/dashboard/<name>/page.tsx`\n5. Create feature components in `src/features/<name>/components/`\n6. Add navigation item in `src/config/nav-config.ts`\n7. (Optional) Add route handlers in `src/app/api/<name>/` for REST API patterns\n8. (Optional) Register new icon in `src/components/icons.tsx`\n\n### Adding a New API Route\n\n1. Create: `src/app/api/my-route/route.ts`\n2. Export HTTP method handlers: `GET`, `POST`, etc.\n3. For BFF pattern: proxy requests to your external backend\n\n### Adding a shadcn Component\n\n```bash\nnpx shadcn add component-name\n```\n\n### Adding a New Theme\n\nSee \"Theming System\" section above or `docs/themes.md`.\n\n---\n\n## Troubleshooting\n\n### Common Issues\n\n**Build fails with Tailwind errors**\n\n- Ensure using Tailwind CSS v4 syntax (`@import 'tailwindcss'`)\n- Check `postcss.config.js` uses `@tailwindcss/postcss`\n\n**Clerk keyless mode popup**\n\n- Normal in development without API keys\n- Click popup to claim application or set env variables\n\n**Theme not applying**\n\n- Check theme name matches in CSS `[data-theme]` and `theme.config.ts`\n- Verify theme CSS is imported in `theme.css`\n\n**Navigation items not showing**\n\n- Check `access` property in nav config\n- Verify user has required org/permission/role\n\n---\n\n## External Documentation\n\n- [Next.js App Router](https://nextjs.org/docs/app)\n- [Clerk Next.js SDK](https://clerk.com/docs/references/nextjs)\n- [shadcn/ui](https://ui.shadcn.com/docs)\n- [Tailwind CSS v4](https://tailwindcss.com/docs)\n- [TanStack Table](https://tanstack.com/table/latest)\n- [Sentry Next.js](https://docs.sentry.io/platforms/javascript/guides/nextjs/)\n\n---\n\n## Notes for AI Agents\n\n1. **Always use `cn()` for className merging** - never concatenate strings manually\n2. **Respect the feature-based structure** - put new feature code in `src/features/`\n3. **Server components by default** - only add `'use client'` when using browser APIs or React hooks\n4. **Type safety first** - avoid `any`, prefer explicit types\n5. **Follow existing patterns** - look at similar components before creating new ones\n6. **Environment variables** - prefix with `NEXT_PUBLIC_` for client-side access\n7. **shadcn components** - don't modify files in `src/components/ui/` directly; extend them instead\n8. **Icons** - NEVER import icons directly from `@tabler/icons-react` or any other icon package. All icons must be registered in `src/components/icons.tsx` and imported as `import { Icons } from '@/components/icons'`. To add a new icon: add the tabler import to `icons.tsx`, add a semantic key to the `Icons` object, then use `Icons.keyName` in your component.\n9. **Page headers** - Always use `PageContainer` props (`pageTitle`, `pageDescription`, `pageHeaderAction`) for page headers. Never import `<Heading>` manually in pages — `PageContainer` handles that internally.\n10. **Forms** - Use TanStack Form via `useAppForm` from `@/components/ui/tanstack-form`. Never use `useState` inside `AppField` render props — extract stateful logic into separate components.\n11. **Button loading** - Use `<Button isLoading={isPending}>` for loading states. Uses CSS Grid overlap trick for zero layout shift. When `isLoading` is not passed, button behaves as default shadcn. `SubmitButton` in forms handles this automatically via form `isSubmitting` state.\n12. **Data layer** - Always go through the service layer: `types.ts` → `service.ts` → `queries.ts`. Components import types from `types.ts`, functions from `service.ts`, query options from `queries.ts`. Never import from `@/constants/mock-api*` directly in components.\n","numLines":755,"startLine":1,"totalLines":755}}}
