active organization.                                                                                       |\nREADME.md:110:| [Exclusive Page](https://shadcn-dashboard.kiranism.dev/dashboard/exclusive)                                                                                            | Example of plan-based access control using Clerk's `<Protect>` component. This page is only accessible to organizations on the Pro plan, demonstrating feature gating with fallback UI.                                                                                 |\nREADME.md:181:##### Clerk Setup\nREADME.md:183:For detailed instructions on configuring Clerk authentication (including organizations/workspaces/teams), please refer to [clerk_setup.md](./docs/clerk_setup.md).\nsrc/config/infoconfig.ts:9:        'The Workspaces page allows you to manage your workspaces and switch between them. This feature is powered by Clerk Organizations, which enables multi-tenant workspace management. You can view all available workspaces, create new ones, and switch your active workspace.',\nsrc/config/infoconfig.ts:12:          title: 'Clerk Organizations Documentation',\nsrc/config/infoconfig.ts:13:          url: 'https://clerk.com/docs/organizations/overview'\nsrc/config/infoconfig.ts:24:          url: 'https://clerk.com/blog/how-to-build-multitenant-authentication-with-clerk'\nsrc/config/infoconfig.ts:43:        \"This application follows Clerk's recommended patterns for multi-tenant authentication. Server-side permission checks ensure that users can only access resources for their active organization.\",\nsrc/config/infoconfig.ts:46:          title: 'Clerk Organizations Documentation',\nsrc/config/infoconfig.ts:47:          url: 'https://clerk.com/docs/organizations/overview'\nsrc/config/infoconfig.ts:60:        \"The Team Management page allows you to manage your workspace team, including members, roles, security settings, and more. This page provides comprehensive organization management through Clerk's OrganizationProfile component.\",\nsrc/config/infoconfig.ts:63:          title: 'Clerk Organizations Documentation',\nsrc/config/infoconfig.ts:64:          url: 'https://clerk.com/docs/organizations/overview'\nsrc/config/infoconfig.ts:77:        'Configure default roles and permissions in the Clerk Dashboard under Organizations settings. Roles define what actions team members can perform within the workspace. Common roles include admin, member, and custom roles you define.',\nsrc/config/infoconfig.ts:80:          title: 'Clerk Organizations Documentation',\nsrc/config/infoconfig.ts:81:          url: 'https://clerk.com/docs/organizations/overview'\nsrc/config/infoconfig.ts:112:        \"The Billing page allows you to manage your organization's subscription and usage limits. Plans and subscriptions are managed through Clerk Billing for B2B, which provides organization-level subscription management with integrated Stripe payment processing.\",\nsrc/config/infoconfig.ts:115:          title: 'Clerk Billing Documentation',\nsrc/config/infoconfig.ts:116:          url: 'https://clerk.com/docs/billing/overview'\nsrc/config/infoconfig.ts:123:        'View and subscribe to available plans through the pricing table. Plans are created and managed in the Clerk Dashboard. Toggle \"Publicly available\" on plans to show them in the pricing table. Common plans include free, pro, and team tiers.',\nsrc/config/infoconfig.ts:126:          title: 'Clerk Dashboard - Plans',\nsrc/config/infoconfig.ts:127:          url: 'https://dashboard.clerk.com/~/billing/plans'\nsrc/config/infoconfig.ts:134:        'Each plan can include specific features that unlock functionality in the application. Features are added to plans in the Clerk Dashboard and can be checked in code using the `has()` function with `feature` checks.',\nsrc/config/infoconfig.ts:146:        \"Clerk Billing costs 0.7% per transaction, plus transaction fees paid directly to Stripe. Clerk Billing is not the same as Stripe Billing - plans and pricing are managed through the Clerk Dashboard and won't sync with existing Stripe products. Clerk uses Stripe only for payment processing.\",\nsrc/config/infoconfig.ts:152:        \"To enable billing, navigate to Billing Settings in the Clerk Dashboard and enable billing for your application. Choose between Clerk's development gateway (for testing) or your own Stripe account (for production). Note: A Stripe account created for development cannot be used for production.\",\nsrc/config/infoconfig.ts:156:          url: 'https://dashboard.clerk.com/~/billing/settings'\nsrc/config/infoconfig.ts:163:        'Billing is currently in Beta and its APIs are experimental and may undergo breaking changes. To mitigate potential disruptions, we recommend pinning your SDK and `clerk-js` package versions.',\nsrc/app/about/page.tsx:43:            <h2 className='text-foreground mb-4 text-xl font-semibold'>Authentication by Clerk</h2>\nsrc/app/about/page.tsx:47:                href='https://clerk.com'\nsrc/app/about/page.tsx:52:                Clerk\nsrc/app/about/page.tsx:54:              , a modern authentication and user management platform. Clerk provides secure sign-in,\nsrc/app/privacy-policy/page.tsx:39:        {/* Auth handled by Clerk */}\nsrc/app/privacy-policy/page.tsx:41:          <h2 className='text-foreground mb-3 text-xl font-semibold'>Authentication by Clerk</h2>\nsrc/app/privacy-policy/page.tsx:45:              href='https://clerk.com'\nsrc/app/privacy-policy/page.tsx:50:              Clerk\nsrc/app/privacy-policy/page.tsx:53:            sign-in, and password management, are managed by Clerk. For detailed information about\nsrc/app/privacy-policy/page.tsx:54:            how Clerk processes and protects your data, please review their{' '}\nsrc/app/privacy-policy/page.tsx:56:              href='https://clerk.com/legal/privacy'","numLines":61}}
